text:
it could've been a regular ad with a newly clean shaven guy suddenly getting that promotion at work, driving that sports car he always wanted, or something else that didn't make sense. 
instead it had a very important message. it wasn't that women are better than men. it wasn't that all men are rapists. it wasn't that you should shave off your beard and become less masculine. 
it was saying be a good person. don't harass, assault or bully anyone. to stand up to the people that do.
the best a man can get = improve yourself. level up. it's not an insult. it's maturity. we should all strive to be better. 
so please, chill the fuck out. ✌️
.

text:
cn: rape, sexual assault, violence 
intentional torts | the punishment of criminals through the criminal justice process can result in outcomes which are unsatisfactory to victims of these crimes. 
people who have experienced:
- sexual assault;
- assault;
- battery; or
- intimidation,
may have potential civil actions arising out of their experience. 
avenues available can include: - a claim for damages
- a claim for criminal compensation 
claims for damages for trespass to the person are potentially more valuable than claims for other types of injuries. this is because victims can claim amounts under a wider range of heads of damage and, in qld, there are more favourable cost provisions under the personal injuries proceedings act 2002 (qld) for intentional acts and sexual assaults.

anche io posso fare la differenza dando il buon esempio, perchè i ragazzi che ci guardano oggi, sarnno gli uomini del domani. noi crediamo nel meglio per gli uomini”. è questo il meglio che un uomo può ottenere? ❔chiede con tono ironico la voce fuori campo, all'inizio del video, mentre le immagini mostrano una banda di bulli inseguire la loro vittima attraverso uno schermo che mostra una vecchia pubblicità del brand.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

join me this sunday for a free webinar to learn about all things feminine leadership.

let me teach you how to lead like a powerhouse, successful woman in today's culture, without reservation and full of confidence, joy, peace, and presence. 
want to tackle some big goals this year? i'm teaching the feminine leadership principles that will help you crush those goals. learn how to get:

traction: move forward on your 2019 goals using tools and practices that actually move the needle.

vision: develop a vision for yourself as a leader, your business, and your career, then determine the actionable steps to achieve that vision.

decisiveness: learn the tools necessary for making correct and swift decisions when presented with a crossroads.

conflict resolution: navigate and mitigate conflict and hard discussions with ease and confidence.

confidence: gain the ability to set boundaries and the skills to maintain them, even when it's hard.

power protection: recognize the things in your life & business that are taking away from your power (power leaks), and learn how to eliminate them altogether. 
join me on sunday, january 20 at 12pm pst for the free webinar that will propel you forward in your business and in your goals.

text:
this is dorothy. she was one of 69 women who went missing and murdered  from vancouver’s downtown eastside. at the time these women were going missing ( in the late 90’s in one year alone, 14 women vanished from this six block radius), authorities ignored this, so i made a decision to speak into the idea of these women being viewed as inconsequential, that they didn’t have a voice. 
so although these paintings can be disturbing, i only painted the truth. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i did not sanitize the subject matter because although all of these women are beautiful in my eyes (and many tears of anguish were shed with every brushstroke over five years), it would do no justice to this horrific epidemic that still exists throughout the world. i did not memorialize these women, instead to me they symbolize true heroes who will create change by shedding light on this tragedy. i want this #artcollection to someday be seen and used within the educational system. i’ve witnessed first-hand the impact of this collection from high school to university levels. i know the power this collection holds.
i wanted to confront society with issues such a not having a voice, and dorothy’s mouth is stapled shut. 
until we as a society, acknowledge our role in women going missing from marginalized community’s, until we shed light on our darkness, change will not occur. 
i urge you to share this post with your brothers and sisters, mothers and friends..
check out the link on my bio for the trailer to the emmy award-winning feature film, #theexhibtion... soon i will give direct access on my page for my followers to view this film and better understand this tragedy. 
it is in my hope and higher purpose that it moves you to #standforsomething, #makeadifference and #liveoutloud
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text: today more bad news. when agencies are reporting your child missing( regardless of how old they are) it’s devastating! i don’t have a fake life like some lecture about, while trying to be inspirational. i choose not to always share the horrible affects of and on my life, nor do i have to post anything personal, i choose to, and know what, the price will be. as forothers, if i remain silent i cause more violence. this is part of addiction and homelessness. if you can justify or hear anyone justify, any woman, being on the streets, the problem is with you.  as for the code phrase, most my kids know what it means; something wicked this way comes. #gabrielladuncan #indyloveartist #addiction #seattle #albuquerque #sayhername #metoo #homelessness #thedrugzombie

😃🎉hi atlanta friends, do not miss this! i am excited to announce my first book has been published and we are celebrating this milestone in my life with a book launch party!🎉 this is not just about celebrating the book, it truly is celebrating real solutions to help protect ourselves as women and girls!💪
i'd ❤️ for you to join us! •
🗣this event is being hosted by the dynamic speaker/author/serial entrepreneur donni wiggins! this is more than a book signing & celebration, this event will include an interactive panel discussion with domestic violence expert/speaker/ author tamiko lowry pugh, counselor/professor/advocate dr. felicia tillman, & actress/poet/activist ernestine johnson-morrison. “f fear” book is ”a modern-day women’s self-defense guide that teaches you how to reduce your risk of attack, take control, & face fear. 
i will be selling and signing copies of my debut book as well presenting an amazing group and special guests to empower you for 2019. you won't want to miss it. 😃if you can't attend the book launch, you can purchase the book on my website directly as well
➡️ www.myempowereddefense.com/shop

about tonda & empowered defense™️:
empowered defense™️ is led my former police officer tonda linsey. she provides self-defense instruction and education to girls and women around the world with a focus on rape escape. students have learned how to decrease their risk of attack, how to fight back and most important how to develop a mindset of self-defense to protect themselves and elevate every aspect of their lives. •

...to sleep.
to dream.
to take a break. 
to unplug. 
to journal. 
to eat before the kids. 
to take a bath. 
to let someone else watch the kids. 
to fail.
to try again. 
to want more. 
to be successful. 
to hold hands. 
to say no. 
to say yes. 
to feel joy. 
to feel sadness. 
to discover you again. ...check out today’s live for my mini inspo session on the thoughts i had while driving today 💭. for some reason they always happen when i’m driving or laying in bed at night, apparently that’s my best creative window. 😁 .
.

text:
я знаю, во что я верю! но я не научился об этом говорить. наверное, надо учиться))) .
когда мы говорим о вере, мы всегда думаем о вере в бога. но есть ещё не менее важная вера - вера в человека. .
когда в человека верят другие, он чувствует за собой поддержку. и с ней он готов свернуть горы. вера в человека определяет нашу жизнь столь же постоянно и глубоко, как и вера в бога.
.
на работе, в бизнесе наш личный успех почти всегда зависит от успешной работы окружающих. что происходит, если мы не верим в своих коллег или партнеров по бизнесу❓
 если мы сомневаемся в себе, то, скорее всего, станем сомневаться и в окружающих и перестанем доверять им. недоверие, пожалуй, главное препятствие на пути достижения общих целей.
.
 с другой стороны, вера и доверие к другим людям раскрепощают нас. появляется возможность браться за новые волнующие проекты, интригующие и привлекающие нас своей сложностью. при этом также высвобождается весь творческий потенциал тех, кому мы оказываем свое доверие.
.
☦️по вере вашей да будет вам❗
.

на работе, в бизнесе наш личный успех почти всегда зависит от успешной работы окружающих. что происходит, если мы не верим в своих коллег или партнеров по бизнесу❓
 если мы сомневаемся в себе, то, скорее всего, станем сомневаться и в окружающих и перестанем доверять им. недоверие, пожалуй, главное препятствие на пути достижения общих целей.
.
 с другой стороны, вера и доверие к другим людям раскрепощают нас. появляется возможность браться за новые волнующие проекты, интригующие и привлекающие нас своей сложностью. при этом также высвобождается весь творческий потенциал тех, кому мы оказываем свое доверие.
.
☦️по вере вашей да будет вам❗

text:
i’ve been super nostalgic recently and that’s likely because anytime i have a big move coming up in my life, my brain focuses on every minutiae of memories instead.
•
i remembered that one year ago i was rehearsing for my first ever attempt at the vagina monologues with some of the most impeccable women i’ve ever met, (like @superj5976 & @jodmull).❤️❤️
•
if you ever have an opportunity to participate in tvm, i highly recommend it, regardless of your theatre experience. the process of learning the roles and knowing the women selected to play each one is humbling.
•
men, if someone you love participates, then you show up too. volunteer to help with the set, marketing, anything... just show up.
•
if you’ve never seen it, look it up and make that experience a priority. support a live production if you can, if not, watch it at home.
•
be uncomfortable and be better for it.
•
thanks to @monatofficial and @jessica_harrell1 for the performance hair. ❤️😂
.
.
.
.
.

text: gillette com o novo vídeo da campanha “the best a men can get”, se aproxima do movimento #metoo (a expressão metoo vem do movimento ‘the silence breakers’, como quebra do silêncio), e traz aos homens a responsabilidade de serem melhores.  a peça produzida pela grey utiliza cenas de bullying e sexismo para questionar o papel masculino na sociedade. no vídeo, os homens são encorajados não só a mudarem suas atitudes, mas também contribuírem na formação de uma masculinidade menos tóxica e mais consciente. o movimento #metoo, citado na campanha, denunciou inúmeros casos de assédio e abuso sexual dentro da indústria cinematográfica e encorajou mulheres no mundo todo a denunciarem casos de violência. confira toda matéria em: http://www.meioemensagem.com.br/home/ultimas-noticias/2019/01/15/gillette-debate-masculinidade-toxica-em-campanha.html  e também no youtube: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kopmueyp3a0&t

text:
don’t allow the people who hurt you with their actions/inactions define your worthiness of love, safety and belonging, honor and respect.❣️ hold fast to the new belief that you are indeed worthy and can create that in your life. as a creator you hold the paintbrush of your life and that you desire.❣️ when you allow the fear and pain to run there show, one can not paint beauty. the handcuffs of victim mode prohibit freedom and acceptance of the spirituality and gift of pain.❣️ pain resurfaces the flaws and cracks in our armour, thus allowing us to mend them and seal the holes of lack, loss and doubt.
pain is a gift as it can mold and fortify us into unbreakable iron.❣️ send love and light to the ones who hurt you for they need it more than the swords hilt to be reclaimed in their holster.
for with this action of love and peace, is when the healing begins❣️ #loveselffirst

text:
waking up emotionally exhausted today. all the positive affirmations will not help this hot mess express.the week has finally caught up to me. making sure the girls get to school on time..(i guess getting to school late is frowned upon 🙄) homework is done, getting the girls to their activities and making dinner... because apparently they have to eat every night 🤦🏽‍♀️, bath time + tucked into bed, baskets full of laundry and endless to do lists. while running a business and a tribe of 400 #bossbabes 
but i think the most mentally demanding job for a mom to endure, is when your babies are in the learning process. how to treat friends, how to be a good friend and how to understand their emotions. picking your daughter up from school in tears because friends are being mean, breaks my heart into pieces. when you’re a mother, you carry every struggle + heartbreak that happens to your kids and mama bear mode wants to come out. 
meanwhile the other child gets caught in a girl fight at school (she was the hair puller 🤭) all in the same week, how. is. that. possible?! so, cheers to the mom barely hanging on this week, i see you and... girl, same! 💆🏽‍♀️
.
.
.
.
.
#heartbreak #inspire #friends #momlife #sahm #wfhm #same #metoo #affirmations #positive #dreams #militarylife #marinewife #hotmess #momboss #selflove #selfcare #mygirls #staypositive

text: more odd ways to describe feminism and how i address certain scenarios personally, by over thinking with weird ideas. keeping hands to ourselves, or in respective ways, not too touchy personally, not trying to be cold, just kinda ehh. uhh, smallness, femaleness, whatever the reason people try touching others, unwelcomingly, and other things i don't understand. mannerism can use that too, for touchy females. some people touch others in picking on ways, sometimes meaning no harm. sometimes people put their hands on me and my immediate thought, is i am a giant, soooo large, taking up so much space over here with my hugeness. must totally be in your way, of just existing and taking up all the room. i don't tell them that, but keeps me from feeling victimised or sexualized. to all my small lady friends. also for all the degrading cruel slurs and impossible standards, i consider everyone a hoe at this point. as in, you can be an adventure hoe, an accomplishment hoe, a foodie hoe, as well as with bad traits, but i prefer to consider us all hoes of good traits. being raped and bullied for addressing it, before having understanding of sex, sexualities, and random identity things, has started this thought process of why everyone is now a hoe in a positive way. equally hoes, men and woman; or equally humans, that have the same potential to be good or bad. survivor blame, judging trauma with no credentials, shouldn't be a thing, but if it's going to be, well, right back at you, in positive or negative ways, with ya thumbs ____ hoe. or we can all start with some common respect for humanness and not go there. for continued safety, you don't need a gun if you get damn good at practice and blindspotting. #freepress #metoo #blacklivesmatter #waterprotectors

have we reached a place today that we are not allowed to discuss certain topics openly?

has discourse changed that drastically?

it seems so — but not tonight.

at 5pm pst noah levine will be the guest on uncivilized unplugged, a weekly live video podcast experience. (link in bio)

you do not want to miss this. noah will be speaking publicly for the first time in months.

join us as we discuss: — how noah built against the stream & refuge recovery — how bdsm and buddhism interplay — noah’s recent allegations, the loss of his position within his own organization, and the #metoo movement

and more. this is going to be a wide open conversation covering the above and any other direction we decide to go. 
unlike most podcasts where you get to hear the polished, edited, after the fact conversation, with unplugged, you get a front row seat to the live show.

please click the zoom link below at 8 pm est on thursday january 17th.

text:
gillette have certainly caused a stir haven’t they?

a few days ago, the company released an advert asking men to be ‘the best a man can be’, dropping their usual slogan ‘the best a man can get’. the advert itself shows men intervening when other men are behaving inappropriately towards each other, towards women, when they excuse the behaviour of boys as ‘just being boys’, when they cyberbully or mansplain something. in short, they’re trying to challenge toxic masculinity in the wake of the #metoo and #timesup movement.

surely it can’t be a bad thing when a large company like @gillette decides to try to tackle an issue like this? well a lot of people have been rubbed up the wrong way! social media was rife with comments like ‘i’m going to boycott gillette now’ and ‘how dare they tar all men with the same brush’. what do you think? is their advert appropriate or do you think they should have left the matter alone?

#gillette #thebestamancanbe #thebestamancanget #cyberbully #mansplain #metoo #timesup #toxicmasculinity #strongwomen #opinion #boyswillnotbeboys  #powerfulwomen #feminist #feminism #bywomenforeveryone #abouttimes

text:
how do we teach our kids tolerance, acceptance, & not to bully?
when those in positions of authority, power, & influence discuss, name call, degrade & bully others?
we must hold them accountable!
we must take a stand for those who are still being oppressed. 
so the next time you catch yourself saying “why are they (meaning people of color) still so angry”, think about it. educate yourself, ignorance is not bliss. you can disagree with someone’s beliefs or politics without degrading, rude, bullying racist behavior.

text: ik europa, dochter van koning agenor, was ontvoerd en verkracht door de almachtige zeus hemzelf. het gebeurde op een mooie zonnige dag toen ik met mijn vriendinnen aan het spelen waren bij de kust van de stad tyros. niet ver van ons waren er stieren aan het grazen. ik keek naar de stieren en zag de mooiste parelwitte stier met kleine glanzende hoorntjes. hij was zo mooi! ❤❤❤ natuurlijk was ik wel eerst bang, want was dit een getemde of wilde stier? je weet maar nooit! maar toch ging ik naar de stier toe en ik begon met hem te spelen. langzaam maar zeker. ik maakte bloemenkransen voor hem, liefkoosde hem en uiteindelijk ging ik op zijn rug zitten, toen het gebeurde. de stier rende naar de zee en zwom verder naar een onbekend eiland genaamd kreta. daarna veranderde hij van vorm en bleek hij zeus te zijn. ik was zo bang! 😨 wat had ik verkeerd gedaan tegenover hem? was hij hier om mij te straffen? had mijn va... hij begon mij opeens te kussen... ik baarde hem later twee zonen: minos, heerser van knossos, en rhadamanthys, heerser van phaistos. dit was mijn verhaal. als jij ook een soortgelijk iets hebt meegemaakt, schrijf het dan in de reacties. veel sterkte, europa #metoo

text:
aproveitando esse dia de #peitonusemtabu também pra mostrar o corpo da mulher sob a ótica feminina nas artes, pq ninguém melhor que a própria mulher pra falar e se expressar sobre seu próprio corpo.

_____ "lucretia", da mestra artimisia gentileschi, italia, século xvii "

_____ "quando adolescente, gentileschi foi estuprada por seu professor de arte, um homem chamado agostino tassi. o caso foi a julgamento, e gentileschi foi submetido a um exame físico humilhante e foi torturada para provar a veracidade de suas pretensões antes que tassi fosse condenado e sentenciado ao exílio.

embora sua história de vida tenha, por vezes, sombreado seu trabalho, gentileschi não deixou que tragédias pessoais atrapalhassem sua carreira. ela ficou conhecida por suas representações dramáticas e realistas de mulheres e violência sexual – trabalho que parece incrivelmente oportuno na era do #metoo. hoje, a aceitação por gentileschi desse assunto desafiador a tornou “uma figura importante no simbolismo da luta feminina contra a tirania”, disse macdonnell."

karachi-amidst the global #metoo storm, renowned actor and director angeline malik has decided to initiate a movement as an advocate to voicing relevant social issues in pakistan.

read more: zalmay khalilzad calls on coas gen qamar bajwa
inkaar karo will be the first of a series of movements that will creatively depict strong women coming together to stand against suppression. she has previously talked on subjects like child abuse and violence against women on a local and international level at appna and wapna conference in the us.

speaking about the campaign, angeline said: “this initiative ‘inkaar karo, hum tumhare saath hain’ says a lot. i have heard many stories and seen a lot due to the nature of my work. it’s hard to say no and it is even harder to speak up and make people believe you. i have brought together a group of strong women who feel the same as i do and we altogether want to convey the message that we hear you, we believe you and we will support you
• • • • •
#inkaarkaro - join the movement, and collectively raise your voice against the suppression of women in pakistan. here's looking at the first teaser.

text:
"be the change you want to see in the world"
-mahatma gandhi

greetings,
we are willing to see a change and we are here in the form of change. model united nations conferences these days are just platforms for school/college going children to roam about the venue and not focus on the main purpose of these conferences, debating and learning. a model united nations conference helps a child to develop life skills through researching, writing, public speaking, problem solving, concensus building, conflict resolution and compromise and cooperation. we want you all to learn these life skills so we are providing you a platform, la paix model united nations.

realizing the importance of bringing a change in this deteriorating environment we are very proud to present to you the 'policy of conduct' which everyone concerned with la paix model united nations will have to abide by. we would request everyone to go through the policy clause by clause and agree to the policy through the delegate application. 
swipe left

regards, 
the secretariat.

text:
power: possession of control, influence or authority over something 
we’re bleeding all over each other here in this world, carrying the bloody burdens of generation’s before us that never broke dysfunctional patterns.  we. are. reacting.  more than likely we have all been wounded by a parent, a spouse, a friend or someone we love. that wounding of our souls gives us the opportunity to either repeat those same patterns somewhere else and to continue to hurt ourselves and others, or to evolve- break them, and then step into our ultimate power: the authority over ourselves. 
so if we react, we repeat. we stay in victimhood, in the cycle of addiction, abuse, dysfunction. but if we do the work and evolve (do not kid yourself, it requires painful work) then we can learn to respond, and then step into our power. this then transfers the power from those that have hurt us back to ourselves. you’re here to evolve, not to repeat.

text: in constantinople, byron and hobhouse were exposed to another side of turkish culture regularly witnessed and as regularly abominated by western visitors. in islamic countries at that time and later, public performances by dancing girls – of the sort the european ballet or music hall provided – were proscribed as unthinkably indecent. instead, transvestite boys performed in public places or at weddings, circumcisions, and other family affairs. byron and hobhouse saw such dances in the coffee houses of galata, the foreign suburb of the city. hobhouse described the performance as "beastly." byron's reaction has not been recorded (louis crompton, "byron and greek love – homophobia in 19th-century england," first pubished 1985) 👁‍🗨 #thegiaour #lordbyron #lgbtq #featurefilm #cinema #pride #loveislove #intersectionalfeminism #transinclusive #transinclusivefeminism #stoptransphobia #stopviolenceagainstwomen #stophomophobia #metoo #ustoo #balancetonporc #timesup #fightlikeagirl

text:
חשיפה מרצון של נפגעות ונפגעי תקיפה מינית
החוק מהווה תיקון לחוק העונשין בדבר נפגעות ונפגעי תקיפה מינית.
"התיקון מבקש להחזיר את הבחירה והשליטה של הנפגעות אם לחשוף את סיפורן - ובדרך שהן תבחרנה לעשות זאת. כיום, כדי לחשוף את הסיפור, הנפגעת צריכה לבקש את אישורו של בית המשפט (!). במידה ותבחר לספר את סיפורה ולחשוף את עצמה על דעת עצמה, היא נחשבת עבריינית שעלולה לקבל שנת מאסר. במקור מטרתו של החוק הייתה להגן על הנפגעות אבל השינויים שאנו עדים להם בשנים האחרונות מחייבים אותנו להתאים ולרענן את החוקים. גם קמפיין #metoo הוכיח לנו שצריך אחרת. אני שמחה שסוף סוף הצלחתי לשכנע גם את הקואליציה וגם את שרת המשפטים, שהתנגדו והפילו את הצעת החוק בפעם הקודמת, בחשיבות הגדולה בהעצמת קולן של נפגעות העבירה לספר את סיפוריהן כפי שהן ב-ו-ח-ר-ו-ת". מתוך עמוד הפייסבוק הרשמי של אורלי לוי- אבקסיס .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#גשר #גשרלגשר #אורלילויאבקסיס #בחירות2019 #בחירות #אורלילוי #זההזמןלהתעורר #ערים #חוקים #כנסתישראל #ישראל #חברתי #הצביעווהשפיעו #קלפי #צעירים #דמוקרטיה #שלטון #שינוי #תקווה

text:
pt.9 age ain't nothing but a number is the debut studio album by american singer aaliyah. it was released under jive and blackground records on may 24, 1994, in the united states. after being signed by her uncle barry hankerson, aaliyah was introduced to recording artist and producer r. kelly. he became her mentor, as well as the lead songwriter and producer of the album. the duo recorded the album at the chicago recording company in chicago, illinois. the album featured two hit singles, including the top ten-charting "back & forth" and "at your best (you are love)"; both singles were certified gold by the recording industry association of america (riaa). one additional single followed in the us: "age ain't nothing but a number". two more singles were released internationally after "age ain't nothing but a number": "down with the clique" and "the thing i like".

text:
in case you are needing a reminder of your value, these are the lyrics from kina cosper’s 2000 song titled, “me”. if you haven’t heard this song before, you can find it on youtube - it’s a great song.  no matter my mood, it improves immensely after i listen to this song.

so, you may be asking, what does this have to do with you?  self-love is possible.  if you can work towards not hating yourself to beginning to liking yourself and to eventually love yourself, you will be more satisfied with your life and happier with your decisions.  it does take time.  it is possible. it is worth it.

if you would like a coach to work with you and help you work on this, click on the link in my bio ➡️ @denisestyer to schedule a complimentary call with me.  there is nothing i love more than watching someone transform from self-inadequacy to self-acceptance and self-love💜

text:
[favorita del 2018]
•
the tale de jennifer fox
•
🎞️ sinopsis: -
.
una exploración de la memoria de una mujer cuando ésta se ve obligada a revaluar su primera relación sexual y sus historias basadas en el autoengaño
•
🔬 opinión:
.
partiré y terminaré remarcando que es una película necesaria, ya que habla de un tema tan sensible como es la (des)construcción de una persona que sufrió un abuso sexual cuando pequeña (basándose en el caso de la propia directora cuando era una niña)
.
no es una película efectista que tan solo nos muestra el trauma de una niña que fue abusada, sino que nos plantea el panorama general, desde el papel de la víctima (la cual fuertemente no se considera víctima) y también de los victimarios (su modus operandi y manejo psicológico)
.
es un ensayo de como esta monstruosa situación influye bastante en la persona afectada, y no en tan solo el lado emocional, sino que también en la totalidad de ella; cuerpo, sexo, alma y memoria (los diálogos con su "yo" del pasado son desconcertantes, tal como toda la película...)
.
su historia es necesaria para comprender mucho más cercanamente a las personas que han sido abusadas y entender, por ejemplo, porqué muchas de ellas tardan en denunciar
•

pairé y terminaré remarcando que es una película necesaria, ya que habla de un tema tan sensible como es la (des)construcción de una persona que sufrió un abuso sexual cuando pequeña (basándose en el caso de la propia directora cuando era una niña)
.
no es una película efectista que tan solo nos muestra el trauma de una niña que fue abusada, sino que nos plantea el panorama general, desde el papel de la víctima (la cual fueemente no se considera víctima) y también de los victimarios (su modus operandi y manejo psicológico)
.
es un ensayo de como esta monstruosa situación influye bastante en la persona afectada, y no en tan solo el lado emocional, sino que también en la totalidad de ella; cuerpo, sexo, alma y memoria (los diálogos con su "yo" del pasado son desconceantes, tal como toda la película...)
.
su historia es necesaria para comprender mucho más cercanamente a las personas que han sido abusadas y entender, por ejemplo, porqué muchas de ellas tardan en denunciar
•

text:
pt.2 age ain't nothing but a number is the debut studio album by american singer aaliyah. it was released under jive and blackground records on may 24, 1994, in the united states. after being signed by her uncle barry hankerson, aaliyah was introduced to recording artist and producer r. kelly. he became her mentor, as well as the lead songwriter and producer of the album. the duo recorded the album at the chicago recording company in chicago, illinois. the album featured two hit singles, including the top ten-charting "back & forth" and "at your best (you are love)"; both singles were certified gold by the recording industry association of america (riaa). one additional single followed in the us: "age ain't nothing but a number". two more singles were released internationally after "age ain't nothing but a number": "down with the clique" and "the thing i like".

text:
never did the possibility that it wasn’t my fault cross my mind, but surely no means no? 
sexual assault affects men and women of all ages, sexual orientations, ethnicities and walks of life. the perpetrator could be anyone from a complete stranger, friend or even a trusted family member. situations may vary from case to case but one thing stays the same, it is never the victim’s fault. 
i still have bad days where all i do is relive it over and over again, taking apart every detail, questioning did i do something wrong, could i have prevented it? it took me a long time to comprehend this but reassurance from my close friends and family reminds me that i should never feel guilty or find excuses to blame myself. 
may 2019 be the year no one has to say #metoo again. 
#sexualassault #survivor #fireroseunitysurvivortattoo

text:
#thursdaythoughts you can now pre-order, "the me too movement of the bible," now @ https://www.amazon.com/dp/b07mtlv47w?ref_=pe_3052080_276849420&fbclid=iwar2z1addhwarfyhe1ni9zckj-7oisbsuoeqife9gcgljpxm-tuv8n5-woys  on instagram click the link in the bio!

#metoo #timesup #muterkelly #godsaystimesup my next book, "the me too movement of the bible." understanding the will of god through the word of god and the me too movement i had great hesitation in writing a book about the me too movement and the bible. in my hesitation, i begin to think that maybe a woman should write this book. in this book, i would be challenged to write about things that most preachers never preach or teach in their bible lessons. the sunday school lessons that are written never deal with the issue of sexual assault. most books that are written in the christian arena never deal with the issues that will be discussed in this book. i am about to write about something that if i came across in a movie, i would turn the movie off because i do not find such matters entertaining even in the world of make-believe movies.

but in dealing with these kinds of issues in real life you can't turn it off. you can't fast forward through the scenes that you don't like in real life. many who will read this book wish they could turn it off or fast forward through the pain. this book is a book written for all the silent victims of sexual harassment and sexual assault. i pray that god will use this book to heal all the hurt and the shame that surrounds these heinous crimes. coming spring 2019 ...take a look at dr. eaton's other books at amazon.com/author/revdrmichaeleaton

pt.4 age ain't nothing but a number is the debut studio album by american singer aaliyah. it was released under jive and blackground records on may 24, 1994, in the united states. after being signed by her uncle barry hankerson, aaliyah was introduced to recording artist and producer r. kelly. he became her mentor, as well as the lead songwriter and producer of the album. the duo recorded the album at the chicago recording company in chicago, illinois. the album featured two hit singles, including the top ten-charting "back & forth" and "at your best (you are love)"; both singles were certified gold by the recording industry association of america (riaa). one additional single followed in the us: "age ain't nothing but a number". two more singles were released internationally after "age ain't nothing but a number": "down with the clique" and "the thing i like".

text:
yazidi survivor demands justice for women raped in vietnam war  january 17, 2019  0
by _ reuters

vietnamese villager tran thi ngai was alone in her home when a south korean soldier forced his way in and raped the then-24-year-old midwife during the vietnam war. “i tried to resist but he took my hand, grabbed me inside the room and closed the door and raped me again and again,” said tran. “he raped when in full uniform and a gun on his body. i was so terrified of him,” she said through a translator.

now nearly in her 80s, the softly-spoken tran said she has yet to receive any formal acknowledgement of what happened to her in phu yen province in central vietnam when two south korean soldiers sexually abused her for years.

the rape of women in past and present conflicts has increasingly come into the spotlight with high-profile women like hollywood actress angelina jolie and human rights lawyer amal clooney working to attain justice for rape victims.

yazidi activist nadia murad, one of about 7,000 women held as sex slaves by islamic state militants, won last year’s nobel peace prize along with congolese doctor denis mukwege for their efforts to end the use of sexual violence as a weapon of war.

speaking at a london event on wednesday held to highlight the plight of vietnamese women like tran, murad said more needed to be done to bring perpertrators of sexual violence to justice. “as these criminals enjoy more rights, freedom and life than the victims themselves, how can we restore dignity to the victims if everyone turns a blind eye to the prosecution of perpetrators and allow them to enjoy impunity?” murad said through a translator. “i call upon the international community to hold its responsibilities to protect women from sexual violence in conflict zones,” she added.

recognition

between 1964 and 1973, about 320,000 south korean soldiers were deployed to fight alongside u.s. troops in vietnam, according to campaign group justice for lai dai han.

text:
taken on november 17, 2017 
or 11/17/2017 at the age of 21
.
.
.
purgatory 
every 7 years the body reproduces new cells for your entire body ... they say cats have 9 lives, a total of 8 attempts to be exact
by thy overdose
by thy noose 
by thy wrists 
its 2019 how many chances does one get before one gives up on themselves and remains stuck in the waiting place?
.
.
.

i can not deny my past selves 
for they come knocking at 3am whispering forbidden affairs
and secrets of the unknown 
waiting for a single tear to shed
like drawing blood from a stone
it hurts down to the bone
.
.
#poetry #darkpoems #youarenotalone #youareloved #mentalillness #iamnotavictim #mytruth #femme #wordswithqueens #femaleempowerment #metoo #noshame #abuseofpower

text:
i remember this day when i decided to play the character of 'aarvi'-a victim of marital rape, the sexual assault no one talks about. i wondered, how'd i ever be able to reflect that pain of disrespect a sufferer feels, time and again, through my expressions. i've never been a victim of any such violence, so how am i supposed to make my story, my portrayal of the character, credible? that's when my friend said, "if you think about it, we're all aarvis, in some way or the other." i was stunned. true. i feel aarvi's pain when i'm minding my own business in public places and men deliberately rub their arms against my body. i feel aarvi's pain when i see middle-aged men salivating at my ripped-jeans or skin-tight kurtis, let alone the time when i wear shorts and dresses. i feel aarvi's pain when my trans/gay friends are touched inappropriately by the male security guards. sometimes, when i see men looking down on other genders, i feel that harrowing disrespect.
'it' happens all the time. no matter where we are, i'm sure majority of us have faced machismo in some way or the other! while travelling in the metro, while attending the concerts, even while walking in the streets in broad daylight! amidst all of this wickedness, iniquity and rascality, a lotus bloomed- #metoo
the #metoo movement took off just so beautifully. energies of women, all over the world, amalgamated in the most enticing way! 
when a woman, so courageously, steps forward, digs her feet in and takes a stand. it is our duty to listen to her and pay attention to her. the next step is to prove the truth as soon as possible. the last step is to chastise the culprit, when i say so, the culprit can be the suspect or the "supposed" victim, either of them! it's high time we let them know that we're not here to perpetuate the patriarchal stereotypes. first, we raise our voices! second, we crucify the deserved! 
irrespective of the gender.
the faux cases are exceptions, but they shouldn't divert us. we need to concentrate on the movement's propagation, for a better world!
#campusprincess2019 #missindia #missdiva #theatreactor #theatre #fightforrespect#endpatriarchy #staywoke #fashiongram#browngirl #brownpride

text:
"feminist theologians believe that it matters who is doing theology.  there’s no such thing as thinking about god in a vacuum; in other words male theologians bring their experience of gender when they talk about god, and so do female theologians.  when engaging with religion it matters what someone’s body is like, what their experience is like and how they’ve been included in or excluded from the church.  christian feminists’ emphasis on experience and context leads them to look at biblical texts, worship services and even personal devotion from the perspective of who is included and who is excluded.
.
there are many reasons why sexism can be so deeply ingrained in christianity.  greek social and philosophical categories that were popular when the church was forming often influenced christian social norms, and thus also colored christian writing and theology.  through years of reinterpretation in sexist societies, ideas that categorized men and women on opposite sides of divides like good and evil, rational and emotional, enlightened and carnal, became common binaries in christian thought and treated as part of the religion itself.
.
feminists have taken a variety of approaches to the bible.  one of the most common is to read problematic passages in light of the liberating message of the bible as a whole and study limiting or violent passages within the cultural contexts in which they were written.  for many feminists, closer study of texts in their historical context leads to a greater appreciation of the bible’s respect towards women, but for some there are texts that remain too disturbing to accept as god’s word.  in that case, another option is to critique the canon (the selection of books that make up the modern bible), especially since women were not very involved in the process selecting them.  theologians then evaluate ancient texts more directly on how they relate to women.  most feminist theologians do take the bible as we know it as the central, normative text of christianity and read it critically, paying close attention to what it says about women, and using imagination and historical research where it fails to mention women at all." -queer grace

text:
object (n) / object (v) by @harlot_johanson , @annaleemarie , & @natalieroseeddings . come see the compelling video and tables in person! on view now in enough. reception next friday jan. 25, 6-8pm.

artists' statement (shortened for ig - don't miss reading it in full at the show): "object (n) – a material thing that can be seen and touched.
object (v) – to express one’s opposition to or disagreement with something.

although everyone experiences hurt and healing differently, some commonalities were found among our own personal experiences with sexual, emotional and domestic abuse, sexual assault, intimate partner violence, and rape. one of the main goals of the film and photo-sculptures is to identify and visually display the various emotional stages contained in (1) being traumatized, (2) coming to understand and acknowledge that trauma has occurred, and (3) our ongoing experiences with the fallout of trauma.

using art to navigate trauma and healing has deepened our understanding of this universal process. we have come to recognize that the hours spent on conceptualization and creation of these pieces have developed us into better and more thoughtful healers. our hope is that object (n) / object (v) mobilizes each viewer in the fight against sexual violence and to further explore these processes within themselves." #metoo #enough #mcaexhibition

“ten short years ago, barack obama became president of the united states, and changed the course of history. ten short years ago, our america was hailed globally as a breathtaking example of democracy, as a rainbow coalition of everyday people marching to the same drum beat. we had finally overcome. 
but did we? .
.
both the presidencies of obama and donald trump have produced some of the ugliest divides in history: horrific racial murders, non-stop mass shootings, the explosion of attacks on immigrants and on the lgbtq community, the rise of anti-semitism and islamophobia, a massive gap between the haves and the have-nots, and legions of women stepping forth to challenge sexual violence—and men—in all forms. .
.
in this gripping new collection of thirteen essays, my mother. barack obama. donald trump. and the last stand of the angry white man., kevin powell interweaves brutally honest personal stories with the saga of america, then and now. be it politics, sports, pop culture, hip-hop music, mental health, racism, #metoo, or his very complicated relationship with his mother, these impassioned essays are not merely a mirror of who we are, but also who and what powell thinks we ought to be.
.
.
.

text:
yep, the title of the email is exactly what i was told by someone when i announced tonight's unplugged guest:
.
”he should be in jail and you shouldn't be talking to him.”
.
well, shit.
.
so much for due process, eh? the internet mob has spoken…
.
have we reached a place today that we are not allowed to discuss certain topics openly or give people we don't like a forum?
.
has discourse changed that drastically?
.
it seems so — but not tonight.
.
at 8 pm est tonight, @noahlevine will be my guest on uncivilized unplugged, a weekly live video podcast experience.
.
you do not want to miss this.
.
noah will be speaking publicly for the first time in many months.
.
join us as we discuss:
.
- how noah build against the stream & refuge recovery
.
- how bdsm and buddhism interplay
.
- noah’s recent allegations, the loss of his position within his own organization, and the #metoo movement.
.
and more. this is going to be a wide open conversation covering the above and any other direction we decide to go.
.
unlike most podcasts where you get to hear the polished, edited, after the fact conversation, with unplugged, you get a front row seat to the live show.
.
why do them live? because it scares the shit out of me and make all my control issues flare up. good fun.
.
link in my bio.
.
see you all tonight.
.
yours uncivilized,
.
traver
.
.
.

text: il y a dix ans, j'étais une gosse paumée. je tentais de me remettre de la perte soudaine d'une personne très chère. j'étais mal dans ma peau, je haïssais mon corps de femme et ce qu'il avait enduré. j'ai commencer peu à peu à m'enfermer dans l'auto destruction, parce que c'était le seul truc qui me faisait planer. la seule chose qui me rendait vivante. et puis sans prévenir, je suis tombée sur des personnes exceptionnelles. des personnes qui ont écouté mon histoire, qui ont su être la avec moi pour m'aider à battre mes démons qui me consommaient à vitesse folle... et aujourd'hui, ces personnes sont encore la, même si ça à pas été toujours facile, même si ça à pas été toujours joli. les années et les événements ont fait que les démons ont reprit leurs place, et m'ont fait perdre ma famille. qu'est-ce qu'une famille si elle ne te protège pas? cette année est l'année de la guérison. cette année, c'est décidé c'est moi qui aurait la peau de mes démons. je vais enfin laisser la cicatrice se refermer et dire adieu à ce fantôme. #10yearschallenge #redhead #redlips #girlwithink #girlwithtattoo #girlwithpiercings #stoner #oldghosts #metoo #selfdestruct #healing #thanksevronforthepeopleimet

text:
a fierce and funny feminist debate is disrupted by a ricochet of bullets. assaulted at every turn, a group of millennial women must decide whether they are ready to put their bodies on the line for each other. good friday tackles #metoo feminism at the intersection of gun and sexual violence. performances begin 2/11. tickets available at theflea.org.
—

text:
my ptsd is triggered constantly. i'm slowly acknowledging that the way i may react to things might not be the healthiest at times.
 i'm learning to be nicer to myself and understand that long ago i was conditioned to react a certain way and that although that might have kept me surviving then it serves me no purpose now. 
nonetheless i'd be a liar if i were to say i don't regress to unhealthy patterns but my perseverance is everlasting.and that brings me back to working on myself daily.. see my life became most valuable when i added two more souls on earth. #ptsd. #metoo #mentalhealth my anger and sadness are my biggest battle.

text:
#linkinbio “professionals and family members can help by taking abuse reports seriously, validating emotions, and asking questions that support rather than challenge. well-meaning listeners sometimes pressure victims by insisting they go to a doctor or file a report, but this can have the effect of further pressuring them or disrespecting their agency. rather, it is better to listen carefully, to show concern, and to think through various options, such as therapy or abuse hotlines. the challenge of sexual assault is complex and difficult, but it shouldn’t remain hidden. we can all work together to support victims and raise awareness so abuse can be prevented and healing can occur (https://bit.ly/2rr8mgq).”
_

text:
support also looks like someone who...
.
invests in your healing
.
gives you space to work through your pain
.
prioritizes checking in on you, just because
.
listens & asks what you need, rather than assuming
.
checks your mess
.
genuinely supports your successes
.
is always a shoulder to lean on, even from afar
.
having a strong support system is vital to healing. having people in your life who can see you, love you and support you through all of life’s mess...that’s what we’re all about. now 20+ years of friendship and a handful of painful life experiences later (both together & separate), we’re committed to building a community of women who can support, encourage, nurture, & empower one another in the same way that we have. tag your support system below!
.
want to join our sisterhood community? click the link in our bio to learn about joining our next retreat—where unbreakable and lifelong friendships will be born.

.
at the last march’s women’s empowerment principles forum held by the united nations (where awlo was represented), the cruciality of women’s empowerment was the focus to attain year 2030 sustainable development goals.
for year 2019, as a member of the united nations global compact awlo is tailoring its goals towards women’s sustainable empowerment. hence, the theme for african women in leadership conference rwanda 2019 is ‘empowered for sustainability’.
.
african women in leadership conference holds this year at rwanda on 4th and 5th april 2019 at kigali marriott hotel.
.
african women in leadership conference is a meeting for strategies and capacity building to advance women's leadership. it engages key decision makers to generate solutions, implement best practices, and build partnerships  for women's development.
awlc mainly engages its first stakeholders - the women, to increase leadership participation. since effective strategies originate from women, through equipment for leadership positioning. .

text:
full video on igtv⁣ or swipe 🥰
⁣
my mission is to share my story with the intent that i may bring hope.  hope for all of us.⁣
whatever it might be; loss of a loved one, an illness, a broken heart, trauma or just a bad day.  we are all survivors. ⁣
⁣
⁣
there are 7.7 billion humans living on planet earth, we have all faced obstacles and they are still ahead.  how do we support one another to collectively survive? ⁣
⁣
⁣
i want to share my story of how i survived and have reconstructed myself into a woman who i am proud to be.⁣
⁣
⁣
here is how i did it.⁣
1.  i chose to become fit physically, mentally and emotionally.⁣
2. to be strong even when i felt defeated, isolated and alone. ⁣
3. to use my voice though others would rather me be silent. ⁣
4. prayer & meditation.  yes i prayed and meditated with the intent to forgive the man who assaulted me. ⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
i also want to thank my amazing trainers, teacher & coaches for pushing me to my limits and beyond.  you thought you were just putting me through a workout but really you have been apart of my healing. ⁣
⁣
🥊 @kevan_watson & @boxnburn ⁣
🎬 @riedmartin ⁣

women are now in the light! that saying “there is always light at the end of the tunnel” has proven to be true and we are now in the ‘after dark’.

enamorada del nuevo anuncio de @gillette llamado we believe: the best men can be. este corto es mucho más que un anuncio, es un golpe bajo al machismo desde el mismo mundo masculino; es una joya ya que llama a los hombres a acabar con la “masculinidad tóxica”, que es la clave del éxito para acabar con la violencia de género, la cosificación y manipulación masculina que le hace el sistema social a los hombres, cuando los deshumaniza y les vende que son una maquina con pene.

la marca aprovecha el momento más importante de la historia de la conversación mundial sobre género y  presenta las denuncias de abuso que sacó a la luz pública el movimiento #metoo y usa una parte del discurso que hizo el actor terry crews en el congreso de los estados unidos, cuando confesó que fue víctima de acoso sexual por un alto ejecutivo de hollywood, en el que defendió una ley sobre agresiones sexuales y le exigió a los hombres enfrentar y combatir los comportamientos tóxicos de la masculinidad.

la campaña busca que los hombres sean conscientes de sus acciones, por lo que muestra situaciones de acoso y discriminación hacia las mujeres, así como el bullying que hacen los varones.

el presidente de la compañía, gary coombe, defendió que al responsabilizarnos mutuamente, eliminamos las excusas por el mal comportamiento de muchos hombres y apoyamos a una nueva generación de hombres buenos, por lo que podemos ayudar a crear un cambio positivo que será importante en los próximos años.

cuando detrás de las marcas dirigidas a hombres que son consumidas por muchos “machos”, hay gerentes de marca, directores, publicistas, mercadólogos y otros profesionales que se unen con la intención clara de usar el poder de su marca para mejorar la sociedad, para aportar mensajes contundentes que sensibilicen positivamente a sus consumidores en un tema tan actual como la deconstrucción de la masculinidad tóxica, tenemos un resultado tan bien logrado como esta maravillosa campaña.

#hackiemoselsistema

text: kicking off 2019 way out of my comfort zone, clashing with @thepiersmorgan who thinks the gillette ad is an attack on masculinity. because they only give you about three and a half minutes to get your point across, i didn’t have the chance to say what i really feel, that in this world of #metoo, prejudice, gendered harassment and every day sexism we need to reconsider what is accepted behaviour. it’s not ok to tell boys who are punching each other that ‘boys will be boys’ in the same way that we don’t just shrug and say ‘well, rapists will be rapists’. we need to treat people as people, regardless of their gender, race, looks and sexual orientation. this advert doesn’t criticise men, it criticises toxic behaviour,  celebrating a more modern masculinity which i find way more attractive. i’m amazed at the backlash to what is essentially a message about being decent people. why are the critics so uneasy about this? being a parent is all about leading by example, modelling the kind of behaviour that you want your children to emulate. treat your peers with the respect that you would want your children to be treated with and don’t be afraid of criticism. i don’t always act in a way that i’m proud of, sometimes i’ll say something or do something that, on reflection, wasn’t the best decision. but instead of becoming defensive, i’ll reflect and think about how i can change for the better. every day i ask my children to be the best they can be while i try to be the best i can be. that’s not perfect and i’m ok with that but i have no problem with an advert that thinks about #thebestamancanbe good on you gillette.

text:
daily dose by media world 2018-19
.
as govt decides to set up panel on #metoo cases, pm modi says must respect women
.
a daughter not only has the right to live but also the right to honour, prime minister narendra modi said on friday, amid a nationwide debate on sexual harassment of women following the metoo online campaign — an issue that his cabinet colleague maneka gandhi said could be taken up by a new committee of former judges and lawyers.
the prime minister was speaking about his ‘beti bachao, beti padhao’ (save the daughter, educate the daughter) programme at a function of the national human rights commission. “some narrow-minded people considered a girl child as unwanted and killed them in the wombs,” modi said in his address, referring to the banned practice of foeticide.
.
the beti bachao, beti padhao campaign, he said, had led to an increase in the number of girl children in states such as haryana and rajasthan.
.
“many innocent lives found their right to live. (but) the meaning of life is not just breathing. honour is equally important,” he said.
.
source: hindustan times
.
credit: abhinav chaubey tybmm (advertising)
.
#csc #dailydose #news #metoo #college #mediaworld #likesforlike

text:
trent’anni dopo tian'anmen. donne e studenti sfidano la repressione

di alessandro albana

il 2019 che la #cina si appresta ad affrontare si è aperto nel segno di due delle maggiori mobilitazioni della recente storia del paese. come mostra la risposta repressiva che le ha coinvolte, la mobilitazione femminista nata sull’onda del #metoo globale e quella studentesca in supporto della lotta di lavoratori e lavoratrici della jasic di #shenzhen si affermano come due delle più interessanti dinamiche di dialettica politica in un paese che non fa i conti con mobilitazioni di massa dalla primavera del 1989. trent’anni dopo tian’anmen e un secolo dopo il «movimento del 4 maggio», un certo fermento sociale lancia segnali interessanti dal sottosuolo della stabilità politica cinese. [leggi l’articolo integrale su www.connessioniprecarie.it]

text:
i got this mug from christmas from my mother-in-law and i immediately read it with snarky intentions. 
people. am i right? 😒

but like my very wise friend lacy once said, “people are the worst …and also the best. i don’t know. it’s weird.” so, this morning i sat down with this mug and saw it in a very different light. that’s because last night a male friend of mine reached out with questions about assault accusations currently making their way through our town. he was vulnerable and sincere. he knew i felt differently and he wanted to hear my perspective. he knew his own reaction was limited by his experience. 
we had the most amazing exchange. i thanked him for reaching out. he thanked me for answering his questions and helping him see a different perspective.

this is how we change the world. 
by caring more about moving forward - even if it feels scary - then staying in the same spot because it feels safe.
by admitting when we have questions without answers.
by reaching out to those who might have the answers even if we know those people don’t agree with us on everything. 
by just trying to better understand.

in other words…
people. am i right? 😍

#hardconversations #metoo #gillette #thebestamancanget #istoaskquestions #invitation #notinstruction #peoplecanbethebest #ifwegivethemachance #pantsuitpolitics

text:
stephen colbert roasts ‘fox & friends’ reaction to gillette ad, airs his own ‘woke’ commercial
#
stephen colbert noticed the uproar over that #metoo-themed gillette ad, so naturally he turned to fox news for a fair and balanced analysis. "now some men did not like this ad, like friendly 'fox & friend' friend brian kilmeade, who ranted about it yesterday morning," explained the "late show" host before playing a clip of kilmeade in action. "so let's point out all the bad things that you might say about men, put them into an ad, make men feel horrible, and then say overpay for a razor," the conservative tv network host said while unloading on the commercial. colbert, however, subtly pointed out that companies advertising with a moral compass isn't exactly new. "wow, he really gets worked up about ads," colbert said, and then referenced the "please drink responsibly" message that is included in all alcohol advertising. "oh, so now i'm not supposed to crash my car into a nursing home, stumble out and puke in the therapy pool? thanks for the lecture, mike's hard lemonade!" colbert didn't spend too much time on the hot topic, but unlike the celebrity haters venting their outrage on tv, he did admit he was "sincerely moved by this ad, especially the…

text:
"in life, when something bad happens to you, your survival instincts kick into overdrive. your experience is placed in a safe, little box, where it can hide forever within you. sometimes, the box leaks… but however embarassing or confusing its leaked contents are - you’re never inclined to release or process your experience in its entirety. the sheer reality can feel deadly (literally).
remember - if you open your box, your life will unfold. in falling apart, you fall together."
thank you for these precious words @meghalicek! one year ago i was just starting to realize the way i was hurt but also that i am much stronger than i thought. love u sister ❤️

text:
i interviewed @isparklei for @madamenoire this week and we talked about how she introduced her whole family to r. kelly not just her niece, hoping that he could help them break into the music industry. she shared how she called cps on behalf of her niece, long before she saw the tape. but most memorably she shared this jaw-dropping story about a personal and disgusting interaction she had with r. kelly in front of her parents. 
god bless her for standing up when no one else would, sacrificing her career in attempts to protect a child, and continuing the taxing work of speaking about the abuse of black girls and women when too many people, within our community and beyond, don’t seem to give a f*ck. 
check out the full interview on @madamenoire
:
:
:
#sparkle #survivingrkelly #sexualabuse #sexualassault #metoo #timesup #muterkelly #protectblackwomen #madamenoire

text:
the #metoo movement has focused public attention on the issue of sexual consent. people of all genders, from all walks of life, have stepped forward to tell their stories of sexual harassment and violation. in a predictable backlash, others have taken to mass media to inquire plaintively if “flirting” is now forbidden. this volume (on sale this may) in the mit press essential knowledge series offers a nuanced introduction to sexual consent by a writer who is both a scholar and an activist on this issue.

#sexualconsent #milenapopova #eks #essentialknowledgeseries #activism #bookstagram #readbooks

text:
what does trauma have to do with relationships and sex?

everything

for most of us, our brain sorts for same.  what looks like, feels like, smells like something that happened before can make us think that irrational fear is actually intuition.  or that someone is fated for us when actually he just looks smells or feels like someone from the past. 
trauma isn’t necessarily domestic violence or sexual abuse though it can be. 
it could also be being betrayed.  it could be abandonment.  we think we’ve dealt with it and then he does or says something that reminds us of what happened?  bam right back to where we were. 
so what’s a smart, successful, facebook happy girl to do?  keep making the same mistakes over and over- or drawing a line in the sand and saying- 
your family issues, dynamics, mistakes
end.  here. 
i see it every day.  high functioning, incredible women who are smart and beautiful and accomplished.  finally healing. 
and then what?  love.  friends.  money.  it spills out in every area of their lives. 
next time you feel the panic of something familiar from the past, breathe.  and then call me ❤️💕💗💚 look at everything you’ve been through and survived.  now let’s heal.

i interviewed @isparklei for @madamenoire this week and we talked about how she introduced her whole family to r. kelly not just her niece, hoping that he could help them break into the music industry. she shared how she called cps on behalf of her niece, long before she saw the tape. but most memorably she shared this jaw-dropping story about a personal and disgusting interaction she had with r. kelly in front of her parents. 
god bless her for standing up when no one else would, sacrificing her career in attempts to protect a child, and continuing the taxing work of speaking about the abuse of black girls and women when too many people, within our community and beyond, don’t seem to give a f*ck. 
check out the full interview on @madamenoire

i will be selling and signing copies of my debut book as well presenting an amazing group and special guests to empower you for 2019. you won't want to miss it. 😃if you can't attend the book launch, you can purchase the book on my website directly as well

text:
there has been a lot of controversy since gillette released its latest commercial, we believe: the best men can be: https://youtu.be/kopmueyp3a0. if you listen carefully, the commercial isn’t judging all men. the script clearly states: “we believe in the best in men to say the right thing; to act the right way. some already are in ways big and small. but some is not enough because the boys watching today will be the men of tomorrow.” don’t feel threatened by this – join in the united front! companies like gillette have a powerful voice that we need to harness in order to ensure future generations of men help empower women to achieve true equality. it’s so important to support companies willing to take a stand for what’s right, without fear of retaliation from people who feel threatened by their messaging. gillette is taking action: www.thebestmencanbe.org.

text:
i honestly don’t think social media is a fair battleground for most arguments or conducive to rational discussion, but…. the reactions to the #gillette advert this week has been something i really wanted to post about, but just wasn’t sure what to say.
then this morning, as i was walking home after doing an f45 class (i was going home to shower so still had the same sweaty kit on, and hair scraped up) i heard a loud whistle. i carried on walking and then heard it again, followed by a shout of “hey sexy!”- yes ladies and gentlemen, on a thursday morning in the middle of westfield shopping centre in 2019, an adult man thought an acceptable way to communicate with another adult female was to whistle at her like she was a sheepdog in training. 
to anyone who this week found the gillette advert to promote reverse sexism, to be feminist propaganda, to be an assault on masculinity…. behaviour like i experienced this morning, and that if i’m honest i have experienced on a near daily basis for the past twenty or so years, is the reason why we need adverts like this to help make people aware that this behaviour is not ok. yes it was a pr stunt that has generated massive publicity, but i love that so many people are talking about this now, and hate that there have been such strong reactions against it by men who are upset, offended, threatened…. and who still think wolf whistling is an acceptable form of communication. 
i don’t hate men. i don’t think all men are like that. but i do think some are. cat calling, wolf whistling, unwanted stares and conversations, fear to walk home alone, groping in bars and nightclubs, overcoming stereotypes, being rejected for a job on the basis of gender, having to state over and over again that no means no….. if you find an advert offensive, you should try dealing with all of this shit on a daily basis. 
thank you @gillette for opening up this conversation, to anyone who has engaged in a healthy debate about it, thank you to all the wonderful, supportive, open-minded men i know (there are many) but to the whistling prick this morning and anyone who still thinks “boys will be boys” is an acceptable defence for anything - it isn’t.
name: Lisa-Jane | PT 🐾 Instructor

text:
one year ago i went for a weekend ski trip to maine, got super drunk and made the decision that i was done treating myself like crap. mentally, physically, and emotionally. ⠀
⠀
i started documenting my health and fitness journey as a way to keep myself accountable and as my account grew, i also found the desire to not only hold myself accountable to inspire other to hope on the journey of self discovery. because any self-discovery story starts with learning discipline and getting outside your comfort zone.. you guys have seen mulan right?)⠀
⠀
my hope and desire is to make you see that you are so so so worthy of all the good things in life.  but in order to feel worthy, you must first make your own instincts worthy of your attention and your effort. ⠀
⠀
i never want you to compare yourself to me. to those of you that say to me, i wish i could be like you... to that i say, you can and you are just like me. just because i've been on my journey one year longer than you doesn't make me any "better." your journey is yours alone. ⠀
⠀
just know i'm here and believe in you 100%. you got this. ⠀
⠀
⠀
⠀

text:
#govermentshutdown 
it's not just about federal employees & their families.
low income families and those living on fixed income or receiving emergency assistance for rapid rehousing, vas program, snap liheap or heating assistance grants, not everyone who receives assistance is #unemployed!!! ....some people may not make enough ...or was left with a plate more than they could bear, "working with the scraps they was given".....outcome of living with financial  hardship in poverty  affects children & families. 
#mentalillness is big in our community & is overlooked. 
but is one of the top main cause of death from #suicide, #depression, #anxiety, coping mechanism & drug addictions. our society thinks if we're  just a little well off than the next & others that we're better!  richer,  happier. and that's not true!
people can judge others circumstances all day... but until you  walked in their shoes! we can't determine could've,  wouldn't, should've,  because we don't know what they been thru, what the next person had to overcome on there own or how far they had to come!  humanity, philanthropy, empathy towards those in need or struggling  emotionally,  financially, and the hardships & burdens that makes them challenge  their purpose, question their integrity.
i want you all to know anyone situation can change at the blink of an eye. we must be willing to help more than talk! about those experiences minor setbacks.  if we're not helping than we are apart of the problem..... contribute  to organizations who is helping a cause that u believe in!!! support charities  that inline with your heart.... our country's leader don't care about our country or the people in it whether black , white, in college or not! he don't care about what people eat how they survive everything is for profit #trump #healthcare #familiesinneed #shutdown #borderwall #awareness #mentalillness #crisis #thisisamerica #thehateugive #conditionalsupport! (i'll help u only if) #nofakefamilesfriends #fakesupport they will talk just to judge #always #remainhumble #staywoke #passhelpalong

text:
abuse is abhorrent! but empowerment is infinite👊🏽👊🏽👊🏽💪🏽🙏🏽!
i finally made the time to watch the 'surving r kelly' 6 part documentary on lifetime... there is much my physical mind and self is processing. at one point i stared him in his eyes and used some  blasphemes threats toward his behavior. because i am a spiritually  aware being, my heart and mind boggled over the idea that these atrocious acts r kelly has performed are not who he is at the core of his spirit. my spirit reminded me to look deeply at the #universallaw of #vibration to remember that this being is living out a karmic debt. also it said, you will not give him your power by spending your evening being hateful and upset towards him.
however, my physical self is like monsters do fall and are eliminated! (see the inward battle 😳😬). anywho i joined the #muterkelly  movement and decided to do my part in ending  and addressing sexual, mental, emotional oppression annnd victimization. @iamlisavanallen said it best "i do not address myself as a victim anymore. i am a survivor" so, instead of physically annihilating r kelly, i'm choosing to inspire,  and #empower empower women to embrace their divine feminine, strengthen their minds by knowing, living, and breathing their #selfworth selfworth! through my advocacy around mental, physical and emotional  wellness and stability, i pledge to offer resources, workshops, insights, etc. building up momentum to stay woke, take a stand in our wellbeing. 
who's with me? 🙋🏾‍♀️ #staywoke #selflove #power #blackgirlsmatter #enoughisenough #endrkelly #alphafemale who would have split him in two🏋🏽‍♀️⚔💪🏽👊🏽👊🏽👊🏽 but i'm  turning a nu leaf and using my meditations to 👳🏾‍♀️🧖🏾‍♀️🛀🏾🙏🏽🙏🏽🙏🏽💚💚💚💚 bring me back to peace, and calm.

text:
we don’t need a big fancy speech. it’s easy to see the state of our union — it’s shut down!
i agree with speaker pelosi — how can you, in good conscience, make the people responsible for keeping our assembled government officials safe — work without being paid???
800,000+ federal workers are now going without paychecks [including some legally required to still work] and countless other americans are feeling the residual effects of this dumb #trumpshutdown. 
out of touch and just plain cruel.
but, why exactly is our government shutdown over american taxpayers paying for the wall — when #mexico is supposed to be paying for the wall? 
i don't give a crap about his fan’s spins and interpretations of what he meant to say, or what he really means… he said:
"i will build a great wall -- and nobody builds walls better than me, believe me --and i'll build them very inexpensively. i will build a great, great wall on our southern border, and i will make mexico pay for that wall. mark my words."
words… marked.
he was very clear and specific. he even put it in writing!
he wants money for his stupid wall?… it's going to have to be in pesos… >>>end of discussion.
the #democrats now have control of the house and will put forth sensible legislation to benefit the people of this country. and, for the first time, will conduct real congressional oversight of #trump… his life will now [and deservedly so] become a virtual and perpetual deep colonoscopy… 
the saudis. abuse of power. corruption. ethics. kavanaugh. tax returns. #russia. obstruction of justice! you name it… we'll really start getting to the bottom of it…all! 
to save #america we must hold to account the inept, corrupt and amoral unindicted co-conspirator in the oval office: #illegitimate #failingpresident #donaldtrump.

text:
the third option offered by the ywca amethyst project allows sexual assault victims to obtain a rape kit, have access to community services for recovery, and choose whether or not to pursue the matter within one year while evidence is preserved, allowing them to focus on their own immediate needs before facing all of the challenges that come with the legal process.

otherwise you have to immediately choose to either wash away the evidence or have the evidence collected and proceed with pressing charges. tough decision to make when you are in the middle of attempting to process what has just happened to you.

text:
rani velu nachiyar (3 january 1730 – 25 december 1796) was a queen of sivaganga estate from c. 1780–1790.
she was the first queen to fight against the british colonial power in india.
she is known by tamils as veeramangai ("brave woman").
nachiyar was trained in war match weapons usage, martial arts like valari, silambam (fighting using stick), horse riding and archery.
she married the king of sivagangai, with whom she had a daughter.
when her husband, muthuvaduganathaperiya udaiyathevar, was killed by british soldiers and the son of the nawab of arcot, she was drawn into battle.
when velu nachiyar found the place where the british stored their ammunition, she arranged a suicide attack: a faithful follower, kuyili, doused herself in oil, set herself alight and walked into the storehouse.
velu nachiyar formed a woman's army named "udaiyaal" in honour of her adopted daughter, udaiyaal, who died detonating a british arsenal.
nachiyar was one of the few rulers who regained her kingdom, and ruled it for ten more years.
in 1790, the throne was inherited by her daughter vellacci.
velu nachiyar died a few years later,on 25 december 1796.

text:
characteristics of high porosity hair: .
. 🌺 the cuticles are wide open. .
🌺 moisture and nourishing substances rush in easily. .
🌺 moisture and nourishing substances also leak out just as easily. .
🌺 high porosity hair is dry, light and undernourished. it is brittle and breaks very easily.
.
🌺  hydration, moisture and protein are essential to the health of high porosity hair.
.
. . *here are some go to natural substances for high porosity hair* . . 🌼 water
. .🌼 100% pure black castor oil . . 🌼 100% coconut oil . . 🌼 honey(a natural humectant) . . 🌼 grade a raw shea butter . . 🌼 mai shanu . . 🌼  vegetable glycerin . . 🌼 raw cocoa butter . . 🌼 100% pure palm kernel oil . . 🌼 100% pure olive oil . . 🌼apple cider vinegar rinse (makes cuticles lie down) . . 🌼 local henna dyes .
.
. . *what are treatments for high porosity hair?* . . 💕 steaming with natural protein substances to promote healing and moisture.
(black castor oil, coconut oil, coconut oil, mai shanu, palm kernel oil, eggs/mashed avocado). .
. 💕 henna (the local henna) dyeing also builds the protein and actually fills the gaps of the open cuticles. be sure to put moisture back in the henna treatment. . .
. 💕 daily grooming with protein oils such as black castor, coconut oil, avocado oil which will ‘heal’ the hair. .
. 💕 raw shea butter is one of the best treatments cos it seals in the oils. pure cocoa butter too. mai shanu is also fantastic! grade a shea butter and grade a cocoa butter  give you an acid level of not more than 4% to get the nourishment needed.
