text:
⚠trigger warning⚠ 
i’ve been putting off writing about this for awhile because it’s not an easy topic to discuss but it’s not talked about enough. the intent of this post is to bring awareness to domestic violence. a few months ago i was beaten by my ex boyfriend, someone whom i trusted & loved. i didn’t know when or if he was going to stop. fortunately, my daughter was in a safe place & wasn’t there when this happened. my injuries included a broken nose, multiple stitches & a head injury. i think it’s important people know that this happens far too often to women & some don’t get as lucky as i do. i truly believe in my heart that there was an angel protecting me to safety that night. it’s appalling how many women have gone through this & will continue to go through this. domestic violence affects people of all socioeconomic backgrounds & education levels. looking back, there were many red flags but at the time i was blinded (if you know me, you know i think everyone has a good heart). i keep asking myself “why, why did this happen to me?” but god knew i could handle & grow from this & hopefully help other women who are going through the same thing. at this point i feel so grateful to be here, knowing i’m not alone & have an army of people behind me. some days are harder than others, but i have my daughter who literally brings so much light into my life. 
i want to be an example to other women, especially my daughter, on how to rise above from something so horrific & become stronger & learn from it. my abuser is currently in jail, & at this point we are praying that the justice system does what it is supposed to do. this isn’t going to stop me from reaching my goals, it will push me harder to live life to its fullest & love everyone around me harder! 
#medspiredarmy

written by: @cassiehengel ©️01/16/2019 all rights reserved. 💕
if you or someone you love may be a victim of domestic abuse, visit: https://www.thehotline.org or call the national domestic violence hotline at 1−800−799−7233. someone is available to help 24/7, 365 days a year. 
tag someone & help raise awareness!

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
dünyaca ünlü tıraş bıçağı markası gillette'in; #metoo hareketine, cinsel zorbalığa, maçoluğa gönderme yapan son reklam filmi büyük tepki çekti. youtube'da yaklaşık 615 bin dislike alan reklam filminden sonra internette gillette'e boykot çağrıları yükseldi. pazarlama perspektifiyle değerlendirirsek; verilmek istenen mesajın doğru olması, yerinde olduğunu göstermiyor. tüm şirketler sosyal sorumluluk projelerinin peşinde, çevreye, insana, sanata bayıldıkları için değil tabii ki. müşteri sempatisini kazanmak önemli ancak şurası bir gerçek ki bu tip duyarlı hareketler daha ziyade kadınlar üzerinde etki yaratıyor. 
neredeyse tamamen erkekler için üretim yapan bir şirketin konudan bağımsız olarak sosyal sorumluluk projeleriyle hedefledikleri satış veya müşteri bağlılığına erişebileceğini düşünmemekle birlikte, seçtikleri sosyal sorumluluk konusunun da cinsiyet rolleri ile ilgili ve ağırlıklı olarak kadınların gündeminde olan bir konu olması müşteri kitlesi içerisinde (youtube beğenilerine de bakılırsa) faydalı olmayacaktır.
erkeklerin çoğuna eşlerinin/sevgililerinin traş bıçağı satın aldığını düşünüyorlarsa belki(!)🙃
mesajda yanlış bir şey yok; tacizi, şiddeti övmemek maskülenliğin karşısında olmak demek değil. yine de traş olursanız daha modern daha hoş görünürsünüz “işte bu adam gibi” tarzındaki reklamlar daha olumlu etki yaratırdı. bu anlamda pazarlama departmanı için gereksiz ya da negatif bir harcamadır ve finansal anlamda başarısızlık olarak görülebilir. pazarlama ekibindeki kadınların ve onların suyuna giden politik doğrucu “modern” erkeklerin de bu reklamda payı olduğunu öngörmek zor değil. ama kadınlar ağda yerine tercih edecek satışlar artacak deniyorsa orasını bilemem🤷🏽‍♀️
yorumlarınız üzerinden konuşalım 🧐

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
each year, millions of women are raped or sexually abused but only a few out of them tell their stories. some of them commit suicide because they believe their honor and dignity had been snatched away from them during the unwanted and shameful act often lasting only a few minutes. research has shown that young female children and women are the prime targets of this crime. many rape victims are still hurting from its shame till this moment while others have ended their lives because they were blamed for being raped. she tells it all is about some aspects of my life while growing up, incidents which i have always felt the need to shout out to families, to other girls /daughters. by taking the bold step of writing this book and being a voice that can be heard, i hope that others as well can make a positive change in their lives by coming out with their stories knowing that it is never too late to take a bold step. being raped or sexually molested is a traumatic experience which could bring one’s life to an end. she tells it all is an eye-opener to every reader that whoever goes through such an experience should not keep silent but dare to speak out for justice to take its course. the laws relating to the offence of rape has been explained in such a way that any reader can understand.

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
today i have a visit with a women's health study that is conducting research on rape victims and their healing process.  this, we hope, will help others heal from truama in the future.  from the moment they asked if i would be a participant i knew i had to say yes, if anything were to come from this helping another would be it...for me it was perfect.
.
but, the study is at the hospital i was brought to in the ambulance the day of the attack...and it brings up a lot of emotions for me.  last time i was there i snapped at someone who was rather rude to me, typically i try not to let things of that nature bother me but that day with where i was at it wasn't happening...i wasn't taking their shit.  thankfully i have my rock, my stable force, my support...my best friend and husband by my side.  he has been amazing through all of this, i couldn't ask for me.  with him by my side holding my hand i know i will be strong.
.

text: “when i show up on my mat with body-based gratitude, everything changes: i move simply because my body craves movement, not a punishment, but a gift. i get to witness what i am capable of, what my body has survived. i get to feel how it is to sit into my strength, to ground into the earth like i could make craters below my feet, to hold myself up, to simply breathe through it all. the picture is so much bigger than any picture could capture. give your body permission to speak louder than the mirror and give your heart permission to observe more than your eyes. know that we are worthy of unlearning falsehoods, of embracing unbound self-love, and of celebrating our bodies incredible resilience on and off the mat” - excerpt from my article on body resilience for @liquidoactive and @the_nedic 🙏 event announcement: so passionate about this work and these messages. excited to be hosting a body image circle & zumba dance workshop on jan 28th with my soul sis @tessa_fitspirit ✨ come dance your liberation & nurture an empowering relationship to physical movement. check my story or dm for details 💚

in order to say yes!

one question for you lovely people. due to the fact they're natural and not pp plastic means they have to be slightly chunkier than the normal lip balm tube (2cm diameter for those that are interested). so please 'like' this post or comment if you'd be happy with a slightly larger container in order to do your bit and help the planet 🙄  what a choice eh and what a leading question, who knew i used to be a research moderator... 😂

pt.5  #dontbanrkellysmusic
in 1994 we all heard kelly got aaliyah pregnant and married her when she was 15 years old. a video tape of r. kelly having sex and urinating on an alleged 14 year old was made in 1999, the tape was leaked to the public in 2000. kelly was acquitted of all charges in 2008 even though millions saw kelly on the video tape having sex with an alleged minor. this performance took place on the bet awards in 2010!

robert sylvester kelly (born january 8, 1967)  is an american singer, songwriter, record producer, and former professional basketball player. a native of chicago, kelly began performing during the late 1980s and debuted in 1992 with the group public announcement. in 1993, kelly went solo with the album 12 play. he is known for a collection of major hit singles including "bump n' grind", "your body's callin'", "i believe i can fly", "gotham city", "ignition (remix)", "if i could turn back the hands of time", "the world's greatest", "i'm a flirt (remix)", and the hip-hopera "trapped in the closet". in 1998, kelly won three grammy awards for "i believe i can fly".his distinctive sound and style has influenced numerous hip hop and contemporary r&b artists. kelly became the first musician to play professional basketball, when he was signed in 1997.

text:
we try not to get too political around here, but sometimes you just need to act on what is right.

starting today, we’ve removed all r. kelly songs from our playlists, and we encourage all of our fellow fitness studios/gyms across chicago to do the same.

the recent #survivingrkelly documentary brought to light wrongs that we as a community cannot ignore - and it hit especially close to home knowing one of his infamous locations is right in our backyard. please stand with us to #muterkelly.

let's set a new level of accountability for how men treat our daughters, mothers, friends, and partners. it's time. 👊🏿👊🏽👊🏻👊🏾
.

today when i refused hugs from men i was questioned. and that’s not ok. my body my choice. if i don’t want to be hugged respect that. if i don’t want you to high five me: respect that. the more i become aware of my boundaries the less i accept disrespectful and rude behavior— actually, no, i have zero tolerance for it. #feminist #feminism #metoo #stayaway #strongwoman #respect #respectme

text:
i hate it when marketing people and other instagram pages try to link women's rights and drinking because women have always suffered from the effects of alcohol historically and were left broke and abused by their husbands after they had spent all their money on alcohol. 
today the rate of alcoholism in women has increased by 83 percent in the past eleven years and the number of women dying from drug overdose has tripled since 1999

but women still push alcohol on other women without thinking about the addiction potential and the health consequences. they exclude moms who don't drink from playdates and leave sober women feeling lost and alone, often times this leads them back to drinking despite the knowledge that alcohol is poison 
we can't continue to have rose all day and wine tasting events at our yoga studios without accepting that we in turn need to provide treatment or be prepared for the aftermath of the addiction we have actively been a part of creating. 
most people are too scared of putting their personal reputation at risk by admitting they had a drinking problem or were addicted and this holds them back from getting the right kind of help or seeing the issue with clarity. 
when we are drinking it feels like everyone else is drinking and lately the numbers don't lie. addiction, death and jail are the results of the increase in alcohol sales.... and the alcohol industry laughs all the way to the bank  as do celebrities that profit from alcohol addiction abuse like @reesewitherspoon who probably could have found an alternative title to her book and @kristenanniebell @jennifer.garner who both have dealt with the aftermath of alcohol addiction and still laugh at alcohol and women on shows like @theellenshow . if they really cared about women they would stop pushing poison and start promoting wellness in the middle of an epidemic of substance abuse in our country. 
let's wake up and stop wasting our hard earned money on the biggest scam, alcohol. 
#drydiet #sober #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #transformation #empoweringwomen #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #transformation #empoweringwomen #addictionrecovery #onedayatatime

text:
yes! that is what you think it is! interesting posts on @cbcradio @dezeen and @designboom this week about the osé robotic massager. .
the mostly female designed sex toy was revoked of the honoree award that it received at the annual consumer electronics show (ces) in las vegas which showcases innovative consumer tech products.
.
the hands-free robotic massager which according to dezeen “imitates the movements and sensations of a human partner, in a bid to avoid ‘buzzing, desensitising’, vibrations” was disqualified from the awards as no products entered can be “immoral obscene, indecent, profane or not in keeping with ces’s image.” .
following an outcry from lora dicarlo, the company begins the product, ces said that the toy didn’t fit into the robotics and drones category in which it was entered, nor any of the other award categories. .
however, according to lora dicarlo, the show “has previously spotlighted male-focused sex tech, most notoriously the ai-powered sex dolls,” and they accused the show of encouraging gender bias and sexism - which is true because i have witnessed it myself. .
coinciding with tumbler’s ban of adult content, i found it interesting to see how tech corporations continue to attempt to control our exposure (or lack of exposure) to sexuality but in fact these controversies actually fuel important conversation and debate. .
.
📸lora dicarlo via @designboom
.
@loradicarlo_hq #loradicarlo #biomimcry #metoo #whydesignmatters

text:
——
quick cardio sesh of 10 minutes.
today was leg tune up💪🏾
(this is second leg sesh of the day including cardio. not lifting heavy first 2 weeks back into it)
——
workout session consisted of:
•seated leg press 4x15 (feet together to hit heads of quadriceps)
superset with:
laying hamstring curls 4x15
(full range of motion with hamstring curls)
(30 seconds to a minute with break time)
•seated abductor machine 4x15
(what’s the purpose? to firm toosh )
remember with this exercise you are moving legs away from center of body using hips. this exercise hits hips to gluteus medius and gluteus minimus.
superset with:
seated adductor machine 4x15
with this exercise you are seated and are moving legs (adductor muscles) towards the center of your body.
this will strengthen inner thigh area and help tone inside leg problem areas.
——-
with my better half @mrs.systm ❤️ ——-

text:
the latest in the spate of bollywood #metoo allegations is a shocker — rajkumar hirani, critically acclaimed film director of such box office hits as 3 idiots, munnabhai m.b.b.s and sanju, among others. 🤯
-
“his accuser, whose identity has not been disclosed publically, was an assistant on the 'sanju,' the director’s latest box office success. in a complaint emailed on november 3, 2018 to the film’s co-producer, vidhu vinod chopra, chopra’s wife, anupama chopra, a film critic and a director at vinod chopra films pvt ltd., chopra’s sister, director shelly chopra, and scriptwriter abhijat joshi. the woman stated that the alleged abuse began on april 9, 2018 and ended in september 2018, during post-production for the film.🎬
-
while the hindi film industry has seen such allegations against prominent actors and directors in the last few months, hirani is arguably the most successful and powerful. the industry’s overall response to the accusations against hirani going forward will be telling of how far bollywood has truly progressed, and how much it is willing to sacrifice to ensure safer work conditions for all, in light of the #metoo movement.”
-
read more about the harrowing details of this accusation and how bollywood has reacted to hirani’s culpability thereof via #browngirl gabrielle deonath — link in bio. share your thoughts in the comments because we need to vent this disgust out together ✊🏽
-

[mengkaji kasus online prostitusi]
[edited version di bio/ swipe up]
teman-teman,
setelah lama tidak menulis, saya mencoba untuk menulis lagi. namun jelas karena sudah lama tidak bermain kata-kata, jadi banyak keseleo saat menulis. tata bahasanya jadi amburadul dan ada beberapa redudansi. kendati demikian, penulis akan senang jika teman-teman mencoba membacanya. jujur tulisan saya bukan dari ide saya sendiri, tapi berdasarkan pemikiran dari para feminis pejuang kemerdekaan ham perempuan dari berbagai latar belakang.  termasuk penyintas prostitusi yang tidak kalah semangat untuk terus mengkritisi sistem yang melegalkan kekerasan terhadap perenpuan ini. 
harapannya berdasarkan kapasitas kita masing-masing, kita sama-sama berjuang untuk memenuhi tuntutan di bawah ini: (1) pidanakan mucikari dan pembeli dalam perdagangan perempuan, serta siapapun yang melanggengan skema perdagangan perempuan, (2) akhiri potensi kriminalisasi pada korban prostitusi, sahkan udang-undang yang bisa menjadi payung hukum bagi korban prostitusi, termasuk undang-undang penghapusan kekerasan seksual,
(3) jamin layanan holistik dan komprehensif bagi perempuan penyintas prostitusi yang hendak keluar dari industri prostitusi,
(4) pastikan kode etik jurnalisme menunjukkan keberpihakan yang jelas pada perempuan dan penyintas kekerasan,
(5) bongkar dan hukum kerjasama antar industri yang melanggengkan perdagangan perempuan, misalnya kerja sama antar industri ,
(6) akhiri marjinalisasi perempuan ke dalam prostitusi, termasuk melalui jaminan pendidikan. rebut kendali atas lembaga masyarakat yang tidak memanusiakan perempuan, sahkan payung hukumーdan payung sosio-ekonomiーagar tidak lagi ada mucikari dan pembeli yang bebas berpesta di atas jeritan, tangisan, dan keringat darah korban prostitusi.

karena setiap korban prostitusi berhak menjadi penyintas yang kontrol atas jiwa dan raganya sendiri terjamin; karena jiwa dan raganya adalah milik ia sepenuhnya, dan bukan orang lain; karena setiap penyintas prostitusi adalah manusia, bukan komoditi.

text:
us-based men’s shaving brand, gillette, released ‘we believe’: a campaign challenging its core demographic – men – to take responsibility for tackling toxic masculinity. the company twisted its classic slogan (“the best a man can get”) into “the best a man can be”, to reinforce its message. achieving 10 million-plus views in under two days this week, gillette’s ad spot referenced the #metoo movement, bullying and other negative male behavior (both towards women and other men) and challenged the ‘boys will be boys’ sentiment. the campaign ended by praising the good men who strive to counteract this aggression.
-
💡heritage heresy. gillette explicitly references its old ads, suggesting that they represent an outdated and sexist view of masculinity. this is a bold move, but a clever one as the implicit message is that ‘we were all guilty of this’, rather than simply lecturing people. we can imagine that calling the brand’s heritage might not have gone down well with some of the more ‘senior’ executives (as it didn’t with the ever-annoying piers morgan!). if your brand wants to make a bold statement about society, then perhaps acknowledging that your history isn’t perfect might help you connect with people, too?
-
📌 spotted in the us 🇺🇸
-

text:
detrás de cada mirada no se esconden cosas tan diferentes, por muy distintas que parezcan. 
con el paso del tiempo descubrí que la peor enemiga de la mujer no es el hombre, es la propia mujer. 
pondremos como excusa a la sociedad, la historia, las leyes o las costumbres, pero siempre terminamos siendo nosotras mismas nuestras propias armas suicidas que no dejamos a nuestro género avanzar en un mundo que, con sus más y con sus menos, está protegido por hombres.
el día que nos queramos y respetemos, el mundo nos querrá como somos. tan distintas pero tan iguales, tan mujeres, tan poderosas... y peligrosas.
si me quiero tapar, me tapo.
y si no, pues no.
pero me tapo por mi.
no por evitar o provocar ser objeto de deseo de ningún hombre.
#andreafergón

•

text:
48! "research states that within 48 hours of running away a child is propositioned/approached by traffickers. traffickers know that a child who’s on the street for 24 hours needs food, shelter and security. they offer this in return for entering into the trafficking life". this is why we have to prevent kids from feeling like they have no where to turn and the streets are their only option. if you can safely shelter a child or help them find safe shelter, you can literally be saving them from being lured into the underworld of the commercial sexual exploitation of children.
if you are a victim or suspect that a child may be a victim of human trafficking, please call 911 or call the national human trafficking resource center at 1-888-373-7888 for help. all victims of slavery and human trafficking have rights and are protected by international, federal, and state law. 
the hotline is: (1) anonymous and confidential; (2) available 24 hours a day, seven days a week; (3) able to provide help, referral to services, training, and general information; (4) accessible in 170 languages; (5) operated by a nonprofit, nongovernmental organization; and (6) toll free. stat from: aba

vi tror också på att män och killar kan vara med och förändra dessa normer och bidra till ett jämställt samhälle utan våld.

i’ve been living a life full of insecurities and low self estime nearly my entire life, which has driven me into a world surrounded even more by superficiality and hypocrisy then real pure love. i have been bullied when i was a teenager to a point i wanted to be invisible, and took me nearly 38 years and one full year of self study to finally be able to accept myself just the way i am today. also being surrounded by other superficial people around me and dealing with a fashion brand with constant exposure to media beauty standards pushed me even more down. you came back into my life the year when i finally found that acceptance and love for myself, with no need to hide between filters, and having the courage to not give a shit any longer about what anyone else thinks about me, but just me. it’s funny because i think timing would have never been better and therefore i truly believe that to find your true love starts first finding yourself and your own love. you make me feel beautiful from the moment i wake up. today i can say, what a relief to have a business involved in real important matters, sharing it with the most wonderful person i have ever met, and a community of compassionated people more conscious about the reality of this world then 95% of the rest of this planet. with all this i want to say thank you, and no matter what, don’t compare yourself never to others and if you are feeling insecure it is probably because you aren’t surrounded by the right people 💚 love, sal p.s. you are not alone ✨ .
.
.

text:
thank you campus princess and @ben_13.nathan for all the exciting group discussions . 
#metoo is a tool which is breaking silence and helping people to win the war. it is not just a movement for women but also children, transgender’s and men. believe me when i say it has nothing to do with feminism or gender equality. it is about reaching out to people for help and finding comfort in the fact that there are other people out there who have been through the same things . 
#metoo has created quite a buzz, not only in india but every part of the  world. people have shared different stories of atrocities they have been subjected to . this has surely given them courage , security and confidence about not being judged by the society. 
not only has the movement exposed the well masked and so called dignified personalities in the industry but also shown a silver lining to the commoners . they now know that  they do not deserve whatever they are being subjected to and there are people who understand their situation. 
but just like a coin has two sides , this movement has its own dooms. it is said that a hundred guilty punished is worse than one innocent convicted .  this movement has also become an attention seeking game for some individuals making it highly difficult to differenciate the actual cases from the false accusations, which tends to dilute the movement. 
however the pros outweigh the cons enormously. #metoo has brought into light the assailants who thought they aren’t accountable to anyone and could do as they please. individuals have finally mustered the courage to stand up for themselves which makes me dream of a more secure future. 
#campusprincess2019  #roadtomissindia  #missindiaorg

text:
"thinking is a process of cumulative experience... even innovative thinking utilises and is dependent upon past accumulations of experience. that body of prior knowledge is a built-in cultural bias." labor laws in the vortex of human rights protection by david ziskind (1985)

it's a little early for #feministfriday, but i wanted to test-run an idea i've been playing with these last few days, triggered by the fact that my dad is coming to visit in a few weeks. my dad visiting means two things. first, that i'm super nervous that his wife won't enjoy herself or won't like things in our new house. second, that the political and social debates that i cut my teeth on as a teenager will resurface.

i love my debates with my dad. he's infuriating and always against everything i stand for and believe in, but i love our debates. the fact of disagreeing with him as a teenager probably helped mould me into the woman i've become.

so i'm readying my arsenal. his views on #brexit have taken a battering; in our last phone debate he conceded to having lost faith in our government's ability to even deliver. so... that leaves feminism, a body of ideas that insults his working class, self-made mindset.

here's the idea i've been playing with. can we argue that traditional concepts of femininity and masculinity are aspects of an in-built cultural bias that has been by centuries of knowledge production led by (predominantly white cis) males?

if thought is a cumulative process, building upon previous thought produced by others, is the only way to achieve gender equality to actively silence (predominantly white cis) male voices for a set period of time in order to let the balance of knowledge production retip in favour of equality?

#qotd: totally open, just tell me what these questions trigger. for me, these questions were inspired by affirmative action policies and quotas for non-males in positions of leadership. 
for the #gradstudents among you, i think the same question can be applied from a postcolonial perspective too, with knowledge production in areas such as security studies and international relations being dominated by white men of europe origin.

#makemethinkthursdays

text: this #throwbackthursday i wanted to do something different. for a long time i didn't love myself, in fact i hated myself. not too long ago i was going through yearbooks with my parents and we found one where i completely scratched my face out. i was 12. my dad was confused. he knew i was difficult then, difficult is probably an understatement, but he didn't actually know. he didn't know because i never told him, i never told anyone. people always told me i was too nice and i needed to be careful because i would eventually be nice to the wrong person. when i got older around the age of 12 and someone started scaring me, daily, i kind of thought it was my fault. i shouldn't have been so nice, i shouldn't have hugged him, i gave him the wrong idea, this is my fault. i spirled, i became violent, depressed, and distant from everyone. it wasn't my fault. it wasn't because i was nice, it was because he is a terrible scary person. a person who is now in prison for beating up his girlfriend as she held their newborn child. i tell you this because i want you to know the truth. if someone is hurting you it isn't your fault, it is not okay, and you do need to seek help. suffering alone may seem easier, it isn't. don't make the mistakes i made. if you are depressed you are fucking human and it is okay. i still struggle some days but it is normal. i am thankful to those people who message me with encouragement and never cross the line, which we all know exists. and if you need someone to talk to, i'm here. please don't continue to struggle alone. you are valued. you are worth it. you are loved. you are so fucking loved #metoo #skyrim #gaminglife #gameaddict #gamerlife  #gamergirl #nerdygirl #picoftheday #youth #gamersofinstagram #instagamer #gamerchick #gamergirls #elderscrolls #playark #twitch #insta #motivationalquotes #truth #depression #positivevibes #love #igers #support #insta #instagram

text:
nakuul mehta: with the #metoo revolution, the glass ceiling has been shattered, voices have been heard 
while talking to a leading daily, ishqbaaaz actor nakuul mehta spoke about the #metoo movement. the actor stated that it is time for men to introspect.
nakuul mehta: with the #metoo revolution, the glass ceiling has been shattered, voices have been heard
last year in september, when tanushree dutta recalled the incident of sexual harassment by nana patekar on the sets of horn ok pleassss in 2008, it led to the beginning of #metoo movement in india. after the movement started in hollywood in 2017, it took a year for the same to begin in india. after tanushree didn't give up on fighting against anyone question her  anyone question her story, it gave courage to many women to speak up and share their experiences and call out the names of sexual predators in the film industry.

text:
🛑boundaries and survivors of childhood sexual abuse..
.
🛑childhood sexual abuse is a boundary of invasion. survivors experience a loss of control over their own bodies and lives..
.
🛑the acts of their trauma have significant enduring negative effects on the development of boundaries. children abused often are not allowed to, or are given the chance to learn their boundaries. when being abused, it leads to confusion over the basic rules of ownership of their body, and learn their body is to be hurt, abused, and manipulated by others.
.
🛑if the child doesn’t receive proper therapeutic services, then the lack of established boundaries will follow them into adulthood. this is one of the many reasons you find many survivors of childhood sexual abuse become survivors of emotional, physical, and or sexual abuse more than once. many survivors also become victims of bullying in schools, and helpless with protecting their bodies from harm.
.
🛑prevention education should be an essential part of parenting. educating yourself, and empowering your children to speak out when someone breaks the body safety rules will help protect them from their boundaries being crossed, and any future abuse... .
.

text:
「ほとんどない」ことにされている側から見た社会の話を。
著 小川たまか

先日「82年生まれ キム・ジヨン」を読んでから、女性の権利とかそういう事に興味が出て、片っ端から買った本を読んでいる。

今作は、性暴力、痴漢、年齢差別、ジェンダー格差、女性視cm、#metoo などの問題について書かれている。

この本を読んで、自分が小学校のときの事を思い出した。確かにやたらと触ってくる男性教師はいた。女子生徒ばかりを触る。
その教師に近づかないよう、女子生徒はしていた気がしたけど、親に相談した子はいなかった気がする。
それが何故だかは全く覚えていないけど。
それから教師なんて、そんなもんだと思い生きてきたし、教師への尊敬や憧れなんて一切無いほど学校が嫌いだった。

そして、今現在は女性差別のある会社で働いている。
産休はない。
子供を産むなら辞めろというスタンスの会社だから。私が尊敬する先輩達も何人も辞めている。
産休は事実上取れないと先輩達にも言われていたから、上司に聞いてみたら"産休はあるよ？ でも産休とって、そのあと本当にきちんと働けるわけ？ 家族のサポートはあるの？ それじゃなきゃ産休とったとしても子供は育てられないよ？"
そう言われた。女性が多く働く職場なのに、こんなザマだ。 そして昨年はドン引きするような事も起きたりした。

今作はいままで、
"しょうがない"
"当たり前だから"
と思い過ごしてきた日々にわずかな問いかけをしてくれる一冊。少しの学びと意識を変えることことで世界が少しだけ変わる事がある。

批判→謝罪ではなく、別の方法でのアプローチもあるということも教えてくれた。

text:
proud to support this great work by @citizensuk @popesylvie @jo_swinson @stellacreasy @womens_aid @fawcettsociety 👏🏼👏🏽 misogyny is hate! .
.
“a coalition of campaign groups and mps have called on the metropolitan police commissioner, cressida dick, to make misogyny a hate crime.

it comes after it was revealed that gender hate incidents were at least as common as any hate crime recorded by police. there were 67,000 such incidents last year, with 57,000 of them targeted at women, according to figures from the crime survey of england and wales. people aged between 16 and 44 were most commonly targeted.

gender was the motivation for more than half of the hate crimes women reported experiencing last year.”
.
.
full story at the guardian. .
.
.
.

text:
100 jahre #frauenwahlrecht. ein grund zum feiern? ja! ein grund, die hände in den schoß zu legen? nein!
denn die wahl zu haben bedeutet nicht, eine emanzipierte entscheidung treffen zu können. die wahl zu haben bedeutet nicht, eine gleichberechtigte wahl zu haben oder mit der wahl für gleichberechtigung sorgen zu können.
frauen können eine kleiderwahl treffen. ihre kleidung hat – das belegen statistiken – keinen einfluss auf die wahrscheinlichkeit, opfer eines sexuellen übergriffs zu werden. wohl aber kann die kleiderwahl dazu führen, sich vor gericht der frage nach einer mitschuld durch "zu aufreizende kleidung" stellen zu müssen.
schwangere haben oft nicht (mehr) die wahl, wo und wie sie gebären wollen. 
frauen haben die wahl zwischen kindern und karriere und vielen erscheint das eine emanzipatorische errungenschaft zu sein. aber sich ausschließlich für die kindererziehung zu entscheiden, bringt in den allermeisten fällen finanzielle abhängigkeit und ein erhöhtes risiko von altersarmut betroffen zu sein mit sich.
hier kann nicht von einer emanzipatorischen wahlmöglichkeit die rede sein.
frauen dürfen wählen, ja. und ihre wahl verschafft zu mehr als zwei dritteln männern eine position in politischen ämtern. der höchste anteil von frauen im bundestag lag bei 37% – und sinkt wieder, zuletzt auf rund 30%. dafür haben wir seit der letzten bundestagswahl einen innenminister, der 1997 gegen die strafbarkeit der vergewaltigung in der ehe gestimmt hat. 
wir leben in einem patriarchalen system und solange überwiegend männer die gesetze verabschieden und in den chefetagen deutscher unternehmen der frauenanteil bei nur 6% liegt, wird sich daran vermutlich auch nichts ändern. 
ja, frauen können mehr erreichen als noch vor 100 jahren. aber auch heute noch ist es für sie mit größeren hürden verbunden als für männer. schaffen sie es in dieselbe position, bringt das nicht zwangsläufig dieselbe bezahlung mit sich. 
die sog. #pay-gap ergibt sich aber auch aus den generellen unterschieden in der berufswahl. dass frauen oft in berufen der "unteren leistungsgruppe" zu finden sind, liegt aber wiederum u.a. in den patriarchalen strukturen begründet.
(weiter i.d. kommentaren)

text:
another democrat just entered the race. sen. kirsten gillibrand, d-n.y., said tuesday that she will run for president in the 2020 campaign.

will she be able to catapult to the top of what’s expected to be a crowded democratic field? others who have said they’re considering running include former vice president joe biden, texas rep. beto o’rourke, and sens. amy klobuchar and cory booker.

gillibrand is known as a prolific fundraiser in the political donor world, and raised just over $1 million from the securities and investment industry during her 2018 campaign, according to the nonpartisan center for responsive politics. lawyers and law firms gave $2.2 million to back gillibrand’s campaign. she finished the cycle raising $17 million and has $10 million on hand.

still, turning to wall street investors and business titans could be a risky tactic in the next election.

#kirstengillibrand2020 #democrat #republican #gop #president #election #trump #trumpadministration #newyork #ny #metoo #womensmarch #women #womensrights #america #government #democracy #freedom #cnbc #cnbcpolitics
name: CNBC
tweet_full:
another democrat just entered the race. sen. kirsten gillibrand, d-n.y., said tuesday that she will run for president in the 2020 campaign.

will she be able to catapult to the top of what’s expected to be a crowded democratic field? others who have said they’re considering running include former vice president joe biden, texas rep. beto o’rourke, and sens. amy klobuchar and cory booker.

gillibrand is known as a prolific fundraiser in the political donor world, and raised just over $1 million from the securities and investment industry during her 2018 campaign, according to the nonpartisan center for responsive politics. lawyers and law firms gave $2.2 million to back gillibrand’s campaign. she finished the cycle raising $17 million and has $10 million on hand.

still, turning to wall street investors and business titans could be a risky tactic in the next election. 
details, at the link in bio. *

text:
i’ve experienced many things over the years of working in trades & never said anything about it for fear of coming across as an “awkward woman” but now my self-confidence is at an all time high & i just don’t give a shit anymore. we need to speak out & we need to make some men change their views & we need to empower women to speak out when something is wrong.
when i was working for that building company last year i was inappropriately touched (more than once) by one of the foremen. when i complained to the 3 company directors about it, they laughed it off & one of them, a centenier no less, excused it by saying that it was because this guy was “old school”! and this is the attitude we’re fighting against! excusing that kind of behaviour as being “old school” or “boys will be boys” is exactly what allows this crap to continue! it’s awesome that gillette have brought out this advert to try to change men’s attitudes but we all have a part to play https://youtu.be/kopmueyp3a0 #femaleplumber #femaletradiesrock #ladytradiesandrockingchicks #toolsandtiaras #bestrong #bepowerful #speakout #empowerwomen #changeattitudes #metoo

text:
okay... it's been a few days since this was released and for some reason greeted with total uproar.

in any comment section or thread related to this video you will see hundreds of people uttering things like 'there is nothing wrong with being a masculine man' and 'men aren't allowed to be men anymore'. yet, watch the advert, and give one example of where it drags down the idea of masculinity. the advert features terry crews for fucks sake, one of the biggest most manly men you'll come across. 
at no point in time will bullying, fighting or misogyny be ingredients for what makes a 'real' man. 
it tackles issues like sexual harassment and bullying... things not exclusive to the male gender, admittedly... but that's irrelevant. it is an advert targeted at men.

if an advert that raises awareness of these issues that are apparent in every day life, is so controversially received, then we are still in a very concerning place.

you don't have to be a raging feminist or a 'snowflake' to have this point of view.

you can be the most masculine man that has ever walked the earth. just do it with respect and don't be a dick.

#gilette
#feminism
#metoo

text:
aiia maasarwe: 
a woman. a sister. a muslim. a palestinian. a student. a traveller. the victim of a random murder and suspected sexual assault. 
how a person can ever think they have the right to another’s body, the right to harm, to take life away from someone, forever horrifies us. 
aiia’s uncle, rame was quoted saying ‘i was very proud of her, she was a very good person, a very loving person.’ let us remember aiia for who she was, for who she would have grown to be, and pay respect to her by demanding safer cities. ‘i can’t believe that something like this has happened in australia. it’s not safe there in australia? in melbourne? it’s not safe?’ - aiia’s uncle.

.

text:
jeg er lige blevet interviewet til avisen om kvinder og kirke. en phd-studerende har lavet en undersøgelse blandt kvindelige præster, hvor 25% har svaret, at de har oplevet diskrimination pga deres køn. og det er selvfølgelig helt nødvendigt, at vi taler om, hvorfor det tal er så højt (også selv om jeg ikke tror, det er så meget højere end andre steder i samfundet?).
det havner bare let det samme sted: at intervieweren bliver så optaget af den åbenlyse ulighed i den konservative minoritets afvisning af kvindelige præster, at hen tror, at det er konservativ teologi, der er årsag til de 25%. men hvis vi virkelig skal tale om diskrimination i kirken, må vi som alle andre steder tale om, hvordan kvindesynet i det hele taget er: fx hvorfor vi synes, at ting er rigtigere og vigtigere, hvis en mand siger dem, eller hvorfor vi er tilbøjelige til at vælge mandlige ledere. eller fx hvorfor alt for damerne laver en kampagne om søstersind, fordi de mener, at kvinde er kvinde værst - og om der ikke er en sammenhæng mellem det syn på kvinder og den tendens, der er til, at menighedsråd helst ikke ansætter udelukkende kvindelige præster i en kirke med henvisning til en ‘hønsegård’.
og hvis vi undrer os over, at de 25% er svære at få til at stå frem, skal vi måske tænke lidt på, hvordan reaktionerne på #metoo har været: at kvinder er blevet beskyldt for heksejagt og er blevet bedt om at være tilgivende.
#kvindesyn #præsteliv

text:
this tough gentleman presented to me unhappy with the hole in his skull. the bone had been elevated to remove a brain tumor but it became infected and the overlying skin was too thin to cover a metal plate after radiotherapy. he needed new skin!
using a technique called tissue expansion a balloon was placed in the front and back of his scalp and slowly inflated over months 'growing' new scalp skin. when there was enough the balloons were removed, the thin skin excised,a metal plate was placed over the defect and the new skin stitched into place.
suffice to say he's a very happy chap! 
plastic and reconstructive surgery continually challenges you, and it's a pleasure to treat such a deserving and grateful patient.
name: Dr Sam Cunneen

text:
,,rant alert. my opinion on the new "toxic masculinity" ad below.

leave your comments about the subject matter below. keep in mind though that any personal attacks against me will remain up for everyone to study.  no i am not afraid of different opinions. yours may help me to clarify mine. #toxicmasculinity. #gillette is either pulling a #publicitystunt (likely) or they're mislabeling masculine behavior as the entire person.

toxic masculinity is an #oxymoron. #masculinity is not toxic. but being a jackass is.

let's call out the behavior of men who act like jackasses, sperm donor, etc. let's not use "toxic masculinity", because of the #nuance of multiple forms of the word.  notice how i said to label the #behavior. #gillette, you once again #fail.

for me there is but one goal: biblical masculinity. jesus called men on the carpet for not treating women with respect, even though (unfortunately) they were seen as property at that time. the psalmist in psalm 31 praised resourceful women. james and john believed mary's testimony about the risen jesus, dropped everything to race to an empty tomb, even though society then would not even consider admitting a woman's testimony in a court of law.

that's good news for men and real #feminism. equality in being treated fairly, because we're all made in the image of god. not to be confused with #equalopportunity or #equaloutcome in our abilities or actions or desire to work hard. that is not always possible. and we certainly need to stop the generalized male bashing. thank you #metoo movement. unintended consequences? maybe. hmm,,... one more thing: this association between clean-shaven and being a decent male: jesus said that it's not what's on the #outside that makes us #unclean: it's what's on the #inside. we can shave all we want and still be a jackass.

live a #dadlife. not life as a #jackass 
and i hope gillette finally figures out what they are giving in to. i have.

p.s. #keoger brand razors and #schickhydro gel gives me a better shave than anything i have ever used from gillette. i won't have to boycott their products, because they're not competitive with other brands.

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
просто задумайтесь
обязательно посмотрите этот ролик от ведущей компании gillete о токсичном поведении мужчин, о угнетении и маскулинности.
для меня этот ролик означает, что мир меняется к лучшему, что все наши усилия, усилия каждого из нас, они очень многого стоят. общество понемногу начинает понимать, что такое личные границы, начинает задумываться об окружающей среде, запрещают цирки с животными в многих странах, ведущие компании отказываются от тестировании продукции на животных, многие бренды не используют мех и кожу.
и это просто потрясающе, осознавать, что мы можем еще все изменить!

gillete присоединилась к компании #metoo против сексуальных домогательств, но мир не фабрика по исполнению желаний, поэтому данный ролик собрал почти в 5 раз больше дизлайков, многие мужчины осуждают его потому что "как мило, что gillette пытается оседлать кампанию "все мужики сволочи", которая захлестнула все основные сми и весь голливуд. лично я теперь, как минимум, больше ваши товары никогда покупать не буду". многие мужчины все еще видят в этом что-то унизительное, что-то, что посягает на их мужественность и этим компания говорит им что делать.

бедняжки, ущемляют их, не все же мужчины такие
❗как это так, нельзя бить девушку? ❗нельзя приставать на улице и настаивать на знакомстве??
❗всех проблем не решить насилием? ❗девушка может быть лучшим боссом?

каждый раз, когда хоть как-то давят на привилегированное положение мужчин, они начинают обвинять женщин/девушек в этом проклятом феминизме, делать им нечего, у вас и так есть право голоса и право работать, что еще надо вам!

text:
good afternoon everyone!

my mornings seems to be great nowadays and the reason behind that is my new family. yes right, i recently got a new family when i qualified in the campus princess auditions held on the 12th of january at iim rohtak. i am really thankfull to @ben_13.nathan sir and the whole team of campus princess to see the ability in me and make me a part of campus princess 2019. 
so as a part of grooming we get different assignments everyday which are not only interesting but also enlightening. 
yesterday we had a group discussion on the topic 'me too campaign- tool to trap or breaking silence to win the war' and i got a chance to share my views with my fellow finalists. i think me too campaign is definitely a step to take to break silence and win the war. any kind of harassment should not be accepted in this country or in the world and people should definitely raise their voices against it. and #metoo campaign has helped many to speak against evil. even many celebrities raised their voices through the #metoo movement which inspired people who kept silent because of the fear of shaming or reputation in the society. no one deserves to get harassed so they must fight against the one who are evil. but everything when misused or taken for granted is a harm. and many have misused this platform to make it a tool to trap. so before reaching on a conclusion or accusing a person, proper investment should be done. no one deserves to get accused for no reason and people should understand that me too movement is not for fun or revenge and not misuse it.

thank you. .
.
.
.
.
#metoo #campusprincess #campusprincess2019

text:
tw: eating disorders, self h*rm, su*cide, calorie counting mentioned in caption. second slide of "body check". •
a large part of me feels ridiculous for posting these photos but another part (the courageous, outspoken part) feels that i should share.
 the first photo was taken january 1st 2015. i was 14 and a half years old, and i hated every inch of myself. this photo i took in the mirror was the very first "body check" photo that i took, in the hopes that i would be able to look back and strive for only improvement in the hopes of reaching happiness via "perfection". what i didn't know at the time was that this was only the beginning of a steep slope that would lead me into weighing myself 5+ times a day, months on end of limiting myself to 700 calories a week as well as self harm and suicide attempts. 
the second photo was taken november 2018 and i think it's my favourite photo of myself ever. i am 18 years and 4 months old and although i fuck up sometimes, i am learning to love who i am. it's been incredibly tough but i now haven't weighed myself in over a year and i am in recovery from both self harm and my eating disorder. i am a happy person and i have learnt that my happiness does not come from the way i look, and that i do not need to punish myself through neglect whenever i make a mistake. 
most importantly though, i am so proud of myself for making it this far ❤️
•
•
if you need to talk to someone do not hesitate to reach out to me!
•

text:
チョ・ナムジュさんの「82年生まれ、キム・ジヨン」読了。韓国で100万部以上のベストセラーとなり、世界的な #metoo ムーブメントとともに社会現象を呼んだという小説。

キム・ジヨンという一人の女性の人生（各年代における具体的なエピソードが章立てで綴られている）を通じて、韓国の女性が社会や男性から日常的に受けているあらゆる差別、不条理を描くという構造。フェミニズム的な視点で性差別を声高に語るものではなく、あくまで“個人”が受けた体験とその悲しみが物語の主軸となっており、自覚の有無を問わず、いかに世の中に女性に対する不条理が当たり前のようにまかり通っているのかに改めて愕然としてしまう。ネタバレになるので詳しくは書かないが、物語の語り手（キム・ジヨン本人ではない）による最後の一文が示す絶望たるや…小説の構造的なテクニックと分かっていても、あんまりだろうそれはと衝撃を受けた。

こうした女性の生きにくさというのは、近年我々夫婦にとっても大きな話題のテーマであり、毎晩のようにこの手の会話になるのだが、気が付けば口調がお互い敵対的になることしばしば。分かっていても「いやそうはいっても男だって」とすぐに比較論に持っていってしまう自分もいるし、無意識下に男性優位の思想を持っていることを指摘されることも少なくない。そしてそれは実際に外れていないし、この本に出てくるエピソードに他人事とは思えない場面もあったのは正直なところ。ちなみにこの本の存在を教えてくれたのは三好さん（男性）で、三好さんも書いていたけど男性こそ読むべき本だと思う。この本は正解を議論するためのものではなく、ただそこにある（女性の）絶望を知るための本。韓国の本だけど極めて日本的。知ることに意味がある。

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

text:
pluto in capricorn art work alert! 'magazine-vandal_witchcraft' is a piece from rebecca scott's exhibition 'dirty pictures' currently on show at standpoint gallery in london. scott takes images from glossy woman's magazines and defaces them to highlight the hypocrisy of our 'so called' sexual freedom. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
since pluto entered capricorn in 2008, the shadow of dominant power systems have been revealed and the #metoo movement is one expression of this purification process. scott's work remind us of one of third wave feminisms important contributions, that of the 'beauty myth,' as coined by naomi wolf. so while we have moved on to more intersectional issues, lets remind ourselves on this important contribution to the movement. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
in 1990, at just 28, wolf wrote 'the beauty myth', a work that pull apart the beauty industry and exposed how its structure seeks to objectify and commodify the then newly empowered generation of women. she pointed out that the pornification of the mainstream media was a backlash against the liberated women of the 70s and had replaced the shackles of domesticity. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
she said '"'beauty" is a currency system like the gold standard. like any economy, it is determined by politics, and in the modern age in the west it is the last, best belief system that keeps male dominance intact.' ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
while the idea that beauty is the last issue that holds women back feels naive today, it is still a pressing issue that both women and men need liberate and may it be so with pluto in capricorn. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
.
on withholding from strangers and male fragility:.
.
"when i was younger, i used to raise my voice and perform “interested,” “fascinated,” and enthralled when i received the signal to do so. .
.
girls are taught early on to invest all of their emotional labor towards showing men that they are “harmless,” “fragile,” and “naive.” .
.
women are expected to act like children, to pretend as if we don’t have experience, to perform co-dependency. .
.
i grew tired of that very long ago - and now if i don’t really know you and we’re discussing business my manner of conversation is generally direct, understated, and to the point." -@mckensiemack
.
🌷🌷🌷🌷🌷🌷🌷🌷🌷🌷🌷🌷🌷
.
girls, women, you do not have to "perform" or silence yourself to preserve a man's ego. what kind of gender dynamics is your conversational vibe reinforcing?
our daughters are listening. .
.
.

text:
meet the only indian at the grammy awards 2019: mumbai’s very own falguni shah
.
 falguni born and raised in mumbai, falu has strong musical roots, receiving rigorous training in the jaipur musical tradition and the benaras style of thumrie.
.
singer-songwriter falguni shah, who goes by the stage name of falu, released an album on february 16, 2018, titled ‘falu’s bazaar’, which has been nominated in the best children’s music category. she is the only indian nominee this year.
.
inspired by her four-year-old son nishaad’s curiosity about language, identity, and the food they ate home, falu’s bazaar overturns a lot of the stereotypes associated with conventional children’s music. besides a high degree of musicianship, the album exudes a great deal of depth and maturity.
.
“i wanted to make a fictional story of an indian child and how he travels from his home to an indian bazaar and discovers many new things and languages. in my mind, i created an indian dora with my child,” says falu, in a conversation with the indian express.
.
“i felt that he needed to be assured of his roots, his identity and culture. there was no better way to answer all his question other than through music (which is a language we all speak in our house),” she adds.
.
her efforts resulted in a 12-song album in hindi, english and gujarati and a grammy nomination. it features her husband, singer-songwriter gaurav shah and her mother, classical singer kishori dalal.
.
source: the better india
.

text:
un spot publicitaire pour les rasoirs gillette surfe sur la vague #metoo et crée la polémique, au point de provoquer une déferlante de réactions courroucées, principalement de la part d'hommes. en cause, son discours sur une virilité "toxique".
l'industrie du rasoir a un problème: la mode hipster masculine a un accessoire devenu incontournable, la barbe, appréciée tant des jeunes "millienials" que des hommes plus mûrs.
.
le marché a en effet passé une mauvaise année 2018, avec des ventes en baisse de 5% en moyenne par rapport à l'année précédente, selon ses propres chiffres. pour tenter de reconquérir ces visages qui l'ont abandonnée, elle a décidé de ne pas attendre que la mode passe.
.
la marque gilette, propriété de la multinationale procter&gamble et leader mondial du secteur, a ainsi sorti une publicité qui surfe sur la vague de dénonciations des violences sexistes initiées par le mouvement #metoo. or, en dénonçant une forme de masculinité "toxique", le spot a déclenché une véritable polémique.

name: Hype.!
tweet_full:
un spot publicitaire pour les rasoirs gillette surfe sur la vague #metoo et crée la polémique, au point de provoquer une déferlante de réactions courroucées, principalement de la part d'hommes. en cause, son discours sur une virilité "toxique".
l'industrie du rasoir a un problème: la mode hipster masculine a un accessoire devenu incontournable, la barbe, appréciée tant des jeunes "millienials" que des hommes plus mûrs.
.
le marché a en effet passé une mauvaise année 2018, avec des ventes en baisse de 5% en moyenne par rapport à l'année précédente, selon ses propres chiffres. pour tenter de reconquérir ces visages qui l'ont abandonnée, elle a décidé de ne pas attendre que la mode passe.
.
la marque gilette, propriété de la multinationale procter&gamble et leader mondial du secteur, a ainsi sorti une publicité qui surfe sur la vague de dénonciations des violences sexistes initiées par le mouvement #metoo. or, en dénonçant une forme de masculinité "toxique", le spot a déclenché une véritable polémique.
.

text:
#10yearchallenge #tenyearchallenge 
ממש לא רציתי להשתתף במשחק פערי העשור הזה, (בעיקר כי האוסידי שלי התחרפן שלא חיכו עם זה לשנה עגולה🤦🏼‍♀️) וגם כי, כן אני נראית יותר טוב ממה שנראיתי לפני עשור ומשהו בי לא אוהב את מחמאת "השתבחת".
אבל סתם בשביל עצמי, גללתי אחורה בתמונות שלי בפייס, ואז לצד תלתלים ג'ינג'ים מוגזמים ובייבי פאט שסירב לרדת, גיליתי ממש רגעים מונצחים בהם לא הייתי אמיצה מספיק. רגעים בהם אמנם קמתי והלכתי כשמשהו הרגיש לי לא בסדר אבל שכעסתי על עצמי בגלל המבוכה, בגלל הסיטואציה, בגלל שהרשיתי שינצלו את התמימות של הילדה שהגיעה לפני חצי שנה לעיר הגדולה ונפלה בכל הקלישאות שאבא הזהיר אותה כל השנים שהן יקרו. 
אז כעסתי על עצמי. 
אין לי כאן איזה סיפור חומל על הילדה ההיא שבא לי לחבק ולהגיד לה איזה יופי גדלת ואת לא אשמה ויהיה טוב יותר. 
כן, גדלתי והתבגרתי ובתחומים מסויימים מגיע לי כיפאק היי אבל פייר, גם היום אני כועסת על עצמי של לפני עשור, והיום, במבט מפוכח אני לא מוכנה יותר להצטרך לסלוח לעצמי בהווה ולא בעתיד. ומקווה שבעוד עשור, אסתכל אחורה ואהיה גאה שלא נתתי לאי הנוחות להשתלט, שעמדתי על שלי ושדיברתי בזמן. 
פערי העשור האלה בעיקר שימחו אותי על מהפיכת #מיטו שאנחנו חיים בה ואהיה אולי שוב קצת תמימה אבל מלאת תקווה שבעשור הבא, #metoo תהיה מהפיכה שילמדו אותה בשיעור היסטוריה והילדים בכלל לא יבינו מה זה הדבר המוזר הזה שהתלוננו עליו ואיך פעם זה היה דבר שבשגרה. *
רק לשם הבהרה:
לאור תמונת ההשוואה, אובייסלי, אין לי שום בעיה עם התמונה עצמה, עדיין חובבת את המחווה לאמריקן ביוטי והייתי בכיף חוזרת על זה גם היום, פשוט ממקום רגשי אחר, בטוח ומכיר את עצמו כמו בתמונה העדכנית.

stop_filter_tweet: ממש לא רציתי להשתתף במשחק פערי העשור הזה , ( בעיקר כי האוסידי שלי התחרפן שלא חיכו עם זה לשנה עגולה🤦🏼‍♀️ ) וגם כי , כן אני נראית יותר טוב ממה שנראיתי לפני עשור ומשהו בי לא אוהב את מחמאת `` השתבחת '' . אבל סתם בשביל עצמי , גללתי אחורה בתמונות שלי בפייס , ואז לצד תלתלים ג'ינג'ים מוגזמים ובייבי פאט שסירב לרדת , גיליתי ממש רגעים מונצחים בהם לא הייתי אמיצה מספיק . רגעים בהם אמנם קמתי והלכתי כשמשהו הרגיש לי לא בסדר אבל שכעסתי על עצמי בגלל המבוכה , בגלל הסיטואציה , בגלל שהרשיתי שינצלו את התמימות של הילדה שהגיעה לפני חצי שנה לעיר הגדולה ונפלה בכל הקלישאות שאבא הזהיר אותה כל השנים שהן יקרו . אז כעסתי על עצמי . אין לי כאן איזה סיפור חומל על הילדה ההיא שבא לי לחבק ולהגיד לה איזה יופי גדלת ואת לא אשמה ויהיה טוב יותר . כן , גדלתי והתבגרתי ובתחומים מסויימים מגיע לי כיפאק היי אבל פייר , גם היום אני כועסת על עצמי של לפני עשור , והיום , במבט מפוכח אני לא מוכנה יותר להצטרך לסלוח לעצמי בהווה ולא בעתיד . ומקווה שבעוד עשור , אסתכל אחורה ואהיה גאה שלא נתתי לאי הנוחות להשתלט , שעמדתי על שלי ושדיברתי בזמן . פערי העשור האלה בעיקר שימחו אותי על מהפיכת שאנחנו חיים בה ואהיה אולי שוב קצת תמימה אבל מלאת תקווה שבעשור הבא , תהיה מהפיכה שילמדו אותה בשיעור היסטוריה והילדים בכלל לא יבינו מה זה הדבר המוזר הזה שהתלוננו עליו ואיך פעם זה היה דבר שבשגרה . * רק לשם הבהרה : לאור תמונת ההשוואה , אובייסלי , אין לי שום בעיה עם התמונה עצמה , עדיין חובבת את המחווה לאמריקן ביוטי והייתי בכיף חוזרת על זה גם היום , פשוט ממקום רגשי אחר , בטוח ומכיר את עצמו כמו בתמונה העדכנית .

text:
trust
abusers have 2 faces. sometimes they walk amongst us, win trust and then privately show their monstrous side. other times they have rehearsed scripts that are used to deceive and hurt. you have seen both sides, it’s a scary place, it causes you to shut down. and then you trust no one again.
h e a l i n g - maybe trust isn’t about the other person, it’s about our trust in ourselves to survive any outcome. the doors to trust open again slowly, practice trust in environments you feel safe. as you trust yourself, your own instincts and awareness of your own potential will also grow. this is the trust that we are looking for.
#journeytolight
📷: @govindgopinath

text: ⚡️hey team!⚡️so i know it’s been awhile since i’ve posted something mental health/ self loving related! i’m really sorry i’ve been mia, i’ve been working 10 hour shifts 5 days a week which is well over 50 hours a week with the occasional saturday shift along with trying to get back to the gym after months of not going. and finally starting my music up again after getting my beloved recording gear! just wanted to let you all know that i’ve been working my ass off to make you guys proud as i have a lot of projects planned for this year, especially around mental health awareness which i can speak publicly about very soon, just a little bit longer until i can! i plan to post more regularly, more so on my ig story about my daily struggles around mental health and self love, it’s just a matter of trying to fit it in around my work schedule but i will make it work! just wanted to fill you guys in with what’s been going on lately and a bit about my struggle last year and why i have moved down to new plymouth for awhile. it’s a hard one to talk about! but all in due time 😇 next post will be about recent struggles and more awareness 🌸💖 #mentalhealth #anxiety #metoo #mentalhealthawareness

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby," said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn
